		<title>Welcome to #Knit Marketing!</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/about__trashed/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 08 Jun 2016 22:19:50 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?page_id=2</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row full_width="stretch_row" full_height="yes" parallax="content-moving" parallax_image="388" css=".vc_custom_1487286574354{margin-top: -62px !important;border-bottom-width: 120px !important;background-position: center;background-repeat: no-repeat !important;background-size: contain !important;}"][vc_column][vc_column_text]
<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-301" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/KNIT-logo-23-e1485125654198-1024x421.png" alt="" width="600" height="247" /></p>
[/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text="SUPERIOR SOCIAL MEDIA MARKETING WOVEN TOGETHER WITH QUALITY JOBS AND TRAINING FOR UNTAPPED YOUTH. " font_container="tag:h3|font_size:28|text_align:center|color:%23ffd700" use_theme_fonts="yes" css=".vc_custom_1488405448788{padding-right: 150px !important;padding-left: 150px !important;}"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width="stretch_row" parallax="content-moving" css=".vc_custom_1473629232253{background-color: rgba(142,193,26,0.62) !important;background-position: center;background-repeat: no-repeat;background-size:cover;*background-color:gb(142,193,26);}"][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="ABOUT US" font_container="tag:h2|font_size:45|text_align:center" use_theme_fonts="yes"][/vc_column][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]
<p style="text-align: left;"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/k4RlFTfM01E?rel=0&amp;showinfo=0" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p>
[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3" css=".vc_custom_1485297750251{margin-left: -10px !important;}"][vc_column_text]
<p style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Montserrat;">Knit Marketing is a Digital Marketing Agency that increases exposure to your target market by empowering a team of young people to produce and manage web campaigns.</p>
<p style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Montserrat;">Services include: social media marketing management, blog editing and publishing, email campaign publishing and monitoring, and website design.</p>
[/vc_column_text][vc_btn title="Contact Us" color="purple" align="center" link="url:http%3A%2F%2Fknitmarketing.com%2Fcontact-us%2F||target:%20_blank|"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width="stretch_row" equal_height="yes" parallax="content-moving" parallax_image="230" css=".vc_custom_1498278261717{background-position: center;background-repeat: no-repeat !important;background-size: cover !important;}"][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="OUR TEAM" font_container="tag:h2|font_size:45|text_align:center|color:%238ec11a" use_theme_fonts="yes"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_single_image image="306" img_size="125x125" alignment="center" style="vc_box_circle"][vc_custom_heading text="Rebecca Borough" font_container="tag:h4|font_size:22|text_align:center|color:%233a3a3a|line_height:1.2" google_fonts="font_family:Signika%3A300%2Cregular%2C600%2C700|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1485298567620{margin-bottom: 10px !important;}"]
<p style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Montserrat; text-align: center;">Founder</p>
[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]
<p style="font-size: 14px; font-family: Montserrat;">As a recent graduate from USC's Master of Science in Social Entrepreneurship program, I was looking for a way to combine my passion for education and youth development with a business plan that would not only serve a social mission, but create real value for companies in need. Knit Marketing is my way of linking social media geniuses with companies who need them, while providing a stepping stone for our team members' bright futures!</p>
<p style="font-size: 14px; font-family: Montserrat;">Connect with me: <a href="mailto:rebecca@knitmarketing.com">[udesign_icon_font name="fa fa-envelope-square"] </a><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/rebeccaborough" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">[udesign_icon_font name="fa fa-linkedin-square"] </a></p>
[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_single_image image="525" img_size="125x125" alignment="center" style="vc_box_circle"][vc_custom_heading text="Adewole Williams" font_container="tag:h4|font_size:22|text_align:center|color:%233a3a3a|line_height:1.2" google_fonts="font_family:Signika%3A300%2Cregular%2C600%2C700|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1513209848939{margin-bottom: 10px !important;}"]
<p style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Montserrat; text-align: center;">Project Manager</p>
[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]
<p style="font-size: 14px; font-family: Montserrat;">Adewole’s passion for technology and graphics led him to independently pursue gigs in graphics design while in college, and after. Currently working for the Los Angeles Conservation Corps, Adewole is deeply committed to improving disadvantaged communities through different state funded projects.</p>
[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_single_image image="567" img_size="125x125" alignment="center" style="vc_box_circle"][vc_custom_heading text="Jorge Guevara" font_container="tag:h4|font_size:22|text_align:center|color:%233a3a3a|line_height:1.2" google_fonts="font_family:Signika%3A300%2Cregular%2C600%2C700|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1513209926003{margin-bottom: 10px !important;}"]
<p style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Montserrat; text-align: center;">Website Guy</p>
[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]
<p style="font-size: 14px; font-family: Montserrat;">As technology and social media become more of an integral part of our world, I believe being able to use both effectively is extremely important. That is why I would like to become a software engineer and become more experienced in the field. As a high school student I still have much to learn. The opportunity to join Knit Marketing perfectly aligned with my goals and hopefully will teach me a lot.</p>
[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_single_image image="566" img_size="125x125" alignment="center" style="vc_box_circle"][vc_custom_heading text="Yesenia Gomez" font_container="tag:h4|font_size:22|text_align:center|color:%233a3a3a|line_height:1.2" google_fonts="font_family:Signika%3A300%2Cregular%2C600%2C700|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1513209892671{margin-bottom: 10px !important;}"]
<p style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Montserrat; text-align: center;">Social Media Associate</p>
[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]
<p style="font-size: 14px; font-family: Montserrat;">I believe life should be about trying new things whenever you can, keeping an open mind is always a useful asset in life. My future goals include becoming a marketing manager which makes Knit Marketing the perfect place for me to be working as an intern. Furthermore, something I really value is giving back to the community, like someone once said, “Being rich isn’t about how much you have, but rather how much you give.”</p>
[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="KEEP IN TOUCH" font_container="tag:h2|font_size:45|text_align:center|color:%238ec11a" use_theme_fonts="yes"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_raw_html][/vc_raw_html][vc_btn title="Sign Up" color="warning" align="center" link="url:http%3A%2F%2Fknitmarketing.com%2Fcontact-us%2F|||"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="223" img_size="full" alignment="right" style="vc_box_rounded"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width="stretch_row" parallax="content-moving" parallax_image="169" css=".vc_custom_1485294982862{margin-bottom: -20px !important;}"][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="LATEST BLOG POSTS" font_container="tag:h2|font_size:45|text_align:center|color:%23ffd700" use_theme_fonts="yes"][vc_masonry_grid post_type="post" max_items="3" grid_id="vc_gid:1520915479174-0792abe4-ed6b-0" taxonomies="72, 40, 18, 19, 17, 12, 7, 59"][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>

<h2>Knit Marketing Launch Party!</h2>
We are excited to announce our official Launch Party and we hope you'll join us! This event is for friends, family, and colleagues of Knit Marketing and for any business owners or marketing managers looking for social media help. Come to the party to learn more!

	<item>
		<title>Homepage - testing</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/homepage-testing__trashed/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 26 Sep 2016 12:43:01 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?page_id=282</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row full_width="stretch_row" el_id="home-hero"][vc_column][vc_column_text]
<h1>Knit Marketing</h1>
[/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text="Superior social media marketing woven together with access to quality jobs for untapped youth." font_container="tag:h3|text_align:left" google_fonts="font_family:Satisfy%3Aregular|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal"][vc_raw_html el_class="event"][/vc_raw_html][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width="stretch_row" parallax="content-moving" css=".vc_custom_1473629232253{background-color: rgba(142,193,26,0.62) !important;background-position: center;background-repeat: no-repeat;background-size:cover;*background-color:gb(142,193,26);}"][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]
<p style="text-align: center;"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/k4RlFTfM01E?rel=0&amp;showinfo=0" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p>
[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_custom_heading text="About Us" font_container="tag:h2|font_size:35|text_align:center" google_fonts="font_family:Montserrat%3Aregular%2C700|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal"][vc_custom_heading text="Knit Marketing is a Digital Marketing Agency, which increases exposure to the teen market by empowering a team of young people to produce and manage social media and blog campaigns." font_container="tag:h2|font_size:20|text_align:center" google_fonts="font_family:Cabin%3Aregular%2Citalic%2C500%2C500italic%2C600%2C600italic%2C700%2C700italic|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal"][vc_empty_space][vc_btn title="Contact Us" color="peacoc" align="center" link="url:http%3A%2F%2Fknitmarketing.com%2Fcontact-us%2F|||"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width="stretch_row" full_height="yes" parallax="content-moving" parallax_image="230"][vc_column width="1/3" css=".vc_custom_1473630680611{padding-left: 20px !important;}"][vc_single_image image="210" img_size="200x200" alignment="center" style="vc_box_circle" css_animation="top-to-bottom"][vc_custom_heading text="Paris Thomas" font_container="tag:h4|font_size:22|text_align:center|color:%233a3a3a|line_height:1.2" google_fonts="font_family:Montserrat%3Aregular%2C700|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1473555117159{margin-bottom: 10px !important;}"]
<h3 style="text-align: center;">Social Media Expert</h3>
[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]
<p style="font-size: 16px; font-family: cabin;">If you're blending positivity, creativity, and spontaneity, then I would be the outcome! I'm a high school senior that hopes to become a forensic scientist and own many small businesses. Along with business, comes marketing and there's no better marketing company than Knit Marketing.</p>
[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_single_image image="208" img_size="200x200" alignment="center" style="vc_box_circle" css_animation="top-to-bottom"][vc_custom_heading text="Rebecca Borough" font_container="tag:h4|font_size:22|text_align:center|color:%233a3a3a|line_height:1.2" google_fonts="font_family:Montserrat%3Aregular%2C700|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1473553807992{margin-bottom: 10px !important;}"]
<h3 style="text-align: center;">Founder</h3>
[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]
<p style="font-size: 16px; font-family: cabin;">As a recent graduate from USC's Master of Science in Social Entrepreneurship program, I was looking for a way to combine my passion for education and youth development with a business plan that would not only serve a social mission, but create real value for companies in need. Knit Marketing is my way of linking social media geniuses with companies who need them, while providing a stepping stone for our team members' bright futures!</p>
<p style="font-size: 16px; font-family: cabin;">Connect with me: <a href="http://www.linkedin.com/in/rebeccaborough" target="_blank">www.linkedin.com/in/rebeccaborough</a></p>
[/vc_column_text][vc_separator][vc_column_text]
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Stay Up-to-Date with News from Knit Marketing!</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">[mc4wp_form id="274"]</p>
[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text][/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3" css=".vc_custom_1473630621369{padding-right: 20px !important;}"][vc_single_image image="214" img_size="200x200" alignment="center" style="vc_box_circle" css_animation="top-to-bottom"][vc_custom_heading text="Nyana Slaughter" font_container="tag:h4|font_size:22|text_align:center|color:%233a3a3a|line_height:1.2" google_fonts="font_family:Montserrat%3Aregular%2C700|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1473555144731{margin-bottom: 10px !important;}"]
<h3 style="text-align: center;">Social Media Expert</h3>
[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]
<p style="font-size: 16px; font-family: cabin;">In life, I feel you need to expand your mind in any possible way and try new things. That is exactly what I did with Knit Marketing. My dream and passion is to be a registered nurse, when I get older, but I wanted to try something different. When I heard about the opportunity to join Knit, I jumped for it, and I love it so much! It's so different from what I want to do, but I wouldn't change doing this for the world!</p>
[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width="stretch_row" parallax="content-moving" css=".vc_custom_1473630880737{margin-bottom: -20px !important;background-color: rgba(255,215,0,0.59) !important;*background-color: rgb(255,215,0) !important;}"][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="Latest Blog Posts" font_container="tag:h2|font_size:55|text_align:center" google_fonts="font_family:Montserrat%3Aregular%2C700|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal"][vc_masonry_grid post_type="post" max_items="10" grid_id="vc_gid:1474894420325-403fddf8-12e6-10"][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Thank you for coming to our Launch Party!</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/thank-you-for-coming-to-our-launch-party/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 29 Oct 2016 23:35:01 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=343</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style = "max-width: 800px; float:none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h1>Thank you for coming to our Launch Party!</h1>
On October 22, 2016, we invited family, friends, and colleagues to join us for our official launch party at <a href="http://crosscamp.us/site/locations/downtown-la2.html" target="_blank">Cross Campus </a>in Downtown Los Angeles and it was a great success! Every corner was covered with the Knit Marketing logo colors, yellow and green, including the banner, flowers, and even our hashtag cupcakes from <a href="http://susiecakes.com/" target="_blank">Susie Cakes</a>! We let people mix and mingle, and then we invited them to watch a short presentation from our team and clients.

<img class="aligncenter wp-image-350" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/IMG_0269.jpg" alt="Knit Marketing Launch Party at Cross Campus DTLA" width="600" height="450" />

<img class="aligncenter wp-image-355 size-large" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/IMG_1615-1024x1024.jpg" alt="Knit Marketing Launch Party at Cross Campus DTLA" width="600" height="600" />

<img class="aligncenter wp-image-344" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/IMG_0248.jpg" alt="Knit Marketing Launch Party at Cross Campus DTLA - Susie Cakes" width="600" height="450" />

<img class="aligncenter wp-image-345" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/IMG_0250.jpg" alt="Knit Marketing Launch Party at Cross Campus DTLA" width="600" height="800" />

<img class="aligncenter wp-image-346" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/IMG_0252.jpg" alt="Knit Marketing Launch Party at Cross Campus DTLA" width="600" height="450" />

<img class="aligncenter wp-image-354 size-large" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/IMG_1613-2-1024x768.jpg" alt="Knit Marketing Launch Party at Cross Campus DTLA" width="600" height="450" />

<img class="aligncenter wp-image-353 size-large" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/IMG_1399-1024x765.jpg" alt="Knit Marketing Launch Party at Cross Campus DTLA" width="600" height="448" />

<img class="aligncenter wp-image-352 size-large" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/IMG_1389-1024x765.jpg" alt="Knit Marketing Launch Party at Cross Campus DTLA" width="600" height="448" />

<img class="aligncenter wp-image-351 size-large" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/IMG_1385-1024x765.jpg" alt="Knit Marketing Launch Party at Cross Campus DTLA" width="600" height="448" />

We were excited to share our progress since we started in June, and eager to talk about our future goals as Knit Marketing. Nyana and Paris gave a great lesson on 10 social media tips, which everyone loved!

<img class="aligncenter wp-image-359" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/14680485_10210312384183465_8364302743397556449_n.jpg" width="600" height="516" />

We were really happy to have our clients and partners, <a href="https://www.barnabasrobotics.com/" target="_blank">Barnabas Robotics</a>, <a href="http://www.medzango.com/" target="_blank">MedZango</a>, and <a href="http://www.imentorglobal.org/" target="_blank">iMentor Global</a> present as well. They had tables set up to display their products and services, and they shared their business stories with our guests.

<img class="aligncenter wp-image-361 size-large" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/20161022_202542-e1486253067448-1024x803.jpg" alt="Barnabas Robotics at Knit Marketing Launch Party" width="600" height="471" />

<img class="size-large wp-image-356 aligncenter" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/IMG_1616-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="600" />

<img class="size-large wp-image-358 aligncenter" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/IMG_4296-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="450" />

<img class="size-large wp-image-378 aligncenter" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_1410-1-1024x765.jpg" alt="iMentor Global at Knit Marketing Launch Party" width="600" height="448" />

We had a great event and were pumped at the end of the night knowing that this is only the beginning of Knit Marketing and the best is yet to come! A super special thanks to our wonderful Social Media Associates, Paris and Nyana!

<img class="size-large wp-image-377 aligncenter" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_1575-1-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="450" />

<img class="aligncenter wp-image-375 size-large" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_1587-1-e1486254322834-768x1024.jpg" alt="Social Media Associates at Knit Marketing Launch Party" width="600" height="800" />

<img class="aligncenter wp-image-376 size-large" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/IMG_1581-1-1024x768.jpg" alt="Social Media Associates at Knit Marketing Launch Party" width="600" height="450" />

Thanks for stopping by the blog and we hope to see you at the next party or workshop. Stay tuned for future events!

-#TeamKnit

	<item>
		<title>What Was Your First Job?</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/what-was-your-first-job/</link>
		<pubDate>Sun, 19 Feb 2017 01:28:05 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=383</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style = "max-width: 800px; float:none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h1>What Was Your First Job?</h1>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><span style="color: #339966;"><em>“A paid job is the exact opposite of supervised transcript fodder like volunteer experiences and internships.  In a paid job, the teen is often working for adults, so she has to cater to them. The adult pays the teen to show up on time, do what is asked of her and more, dress appropriately, be respectful, keep her work area neat, avoid procrastination, tolerate criticism (even unfair criticism)...” - <a style="color: #339966;" href="http://www.wendymogel.com/books/b_minus" target="_blank">Wendy Mogel</a></em></span></p>
One of the things that makes Knit Marketing special is our commitment to hiring and training young people, which means that for most of our employees, Knit will be their first job!

<img class="size-large wp-image-414 aligncenter" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/20160612_170332-1024x725.jpg" alt="Knit Marketing - Team Knit - Teen Jobs" width="600" height="425" />

Do you remember your first paycheck? Do you remember what it was like to put on a uniform, clock-in, or worst of all turn down your friends' invitations, because you <em>had </em>to work? Our founder, Rebecca's first position was a party hostess at a local rollerskating rink, where she served pizza, cake, and soda to kids on roller blades. In high school, she also worked at a retail store in the mall, and at her church as an administrative assistant.

Having a job teaches teens responsibility. It teaches them about the value of dollar and how to manage their time. It helps their parents, because they have extra spending money to go to the movies or buy the shoes they've been eyeing. But more than anything, a first job opens the door to a second job and a third. It may seem like simply counting change or folding clothes, but those experiences slowly but surely add to a list of skills that are not always acquired in grade school. Being forced to work alongside people who may or may not be "friends" and learning to take direction from higher ups, who aren't their parents or their teachers are just a couple of the building blocks of adulthood. The soft skills gained from teen jobs; the independence, confidence, and communication skills are the things that will prepare them for college, their future careers, and their personal and professional relationships.

At our Launch Party, we asked our guests to remember their first jobs and we had a great time learning where everyone got their start. Below are just a few of the teen jobs that our guests had!

<img class="size-large wp-image-406 aligncenter" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/IMG_1559-1-1024x768.jpg" alt="First jobs - teen jobs - Knit Marketing" width="600" height="450" />

<img class="size-large wp-image-405 aligncenter" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/IMG_1562-1-1024x768.jpg" alt="First jobs - teen jobs - Knit Marketing" width="600" height="450" />

<img class="size-large wp-image-403 aligncenter" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/IMG_1565-1-1024x768.jpg" alt="First jobs - teen jobs - Knit Marketing" width="600" height="450" />

<img class="size-large wp-image-402 aligncenter" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/IMG_1568-1-1024x768.jpg" alt="First jobs - teen jobs - Knit Marketing" width="600" height="450" />

<img class="size-large wp-image-401 aligncenter" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/IMG_1571-1-1024x768.jpg" alt="First jobs - teen jobs - Knit Marketing" width="600" height="450" />

<img class="size-large wp-image-400 aligncenter" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/IMG_1573-1-1024x768.jpg" alt="First jobs - teen jobs - Knit Marketing" width="600" height="450" />

Knit Marketing is proud to offer first jobs to many teens and excited to see where a part time job in social media marketing will lead our employees!

Thanks for stopping by and reading our blog.

<img class="size-large wp-image-415 aligncenter" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/20170204_135806_001-1024x576.jpg" alt="Knit Marketing - Team Knit - Teen Jobs" width="600" height="338" />

-#TeamKnit
</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Getting Started</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/getting-started/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 28 Feb 2017 02:21:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=446</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style = "max-width: 800px; float:none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h1>Getting Started</h1>
A common challenge we hear from entrepreneurs and startup teams (our own team included) is not knowing when or where or <strong>how to get started</strong>.

Sometimes, it's because the entrepreneur left a full-time structured job and suddenly finds him/herself wondering how to manage time. For some, it's a question of juggling full-time work and a side hustle and not knowing when to fit it in. Or maybe the startup was born in a school setting, as a group project with mandatory deadlines, 10-slide-deck templates, and lots of support from professors and mentors, and now the team finds themselves asking how to get started in the real world.<img class=" wp-image-453 alignright" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/002.jpg" alt="Do you like my hat? Entrepreneur deciding which hat to wear. " width="247" height="328" />

The startup team goes from having to wear one or few hats to wearing several, and it's hard to know which hat to put on each day. It becomes so overwhelming deciding which hat to wear, that a 40-hour work week starts to sound appealing.

<strong>Don't do it! </strong>

In a new podcast called "<a href="https://www.facebook.com/dontkeepyourdayjob/" target="_blank">Don't Keep Your Day Job</a>," Cathy Heller encourages anyone with a dream to pursue it, and we at Knit Marketing agree.

In their daily <a href="http://us1.campaign-archive2.com/?u=028de8672d5f9a229f15e9edf&amp;id=f8f8908d15&amp;e=1f9b7da6e3" target="_blank">email</a>, Gaping Void suggests starting small in the in-between time. Their advice is about writing, but entrepreneurship is the same. It's like a diet that you never call a diet; you call it a <em>lifestyle. </em>(Supposedly that's going to make you feel better about eating kale.)

<img class="size-full wp-image-447 aligncenter" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/unnamed.jpg" alt="Just Begin from Gaping Void" width="852" height="669" />With any lifestyle change that's going to last, you have to make it manageable for you and your team. Can you fit in a new blog post once a week or a sales call twice a month? While you're sitting in traffic, could you record your brilliant ideas into a voice recorder? Can you outsource the things you don't like doing to friends, family, and other like-minded businesses?

Writers complain about writer's block, but entrepreneurs suffer from the same. The writers' solution is to encourage writing a little bit every day. What small thing can you do for your business each day? We'd love to hear your stories in the comments below!

Thanks so much for stopping by!

-#TeamKnit
<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>
</div>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>A Yummy Afternoon at Melissa&#039;s Produce</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/a-yummy-afternoon-at-melissas-produce/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 07 Mar 2017 18:33:04 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=463</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style = "max-width: 800px; float:none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h1>A Yummy Afternoon at Melissa's Produce</h1>
One of the best things about our work at Knit Marketing is that we get to attend events from lots of different industries. While we're out researching for the latest trends and meeting influencers in our clients' worlds, we get to have a little fun ourselves.

And when it involves food, it's even better!

[caption id="attachment_464" align="aligncenter" width="700"]<img class="wp-image-464" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/IMG_0060-1024x683.jpg" alt="Melissa's Produce and Raghavan Iyer" width="700" height="467" /> Photo Credit: Melissa's Produce[/caption]

Last week, I had the pleasure of attending a wonderful live cooking demo and lunch at <a href="http://www.melissas.com/" target="_blank">Melissa's Produce</a>. Chef <a href="http://www.raghavaniyer.com/" target="_blank">Raghavan Iyer</a> made a marvelous spread of potatoey goodness. We tried 6 delicious recipes from Raghavan's new book <em><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/076118547X?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=workmanpublis-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325&amp;creativeASIN=076118547X" target="_blank">Smashed, Mashed, Boiled, and Baked</a>.</em>

[caption id="attachment_466" align="aligncenter" width="700"]<img class="wp-image-466" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/2017-03-07_0001.jpg" alt="Raghavan Iyer and Melissa's Produce" width="700" height="778" /> Potato Lasagna, Cheesy Tarragon Tots, Crispy Potato Skins, Smashed, Mashed, Boiled, and Baked Book, Sweet Potato Rolls, Thick Cut Potato Crisps with Dark Chocolate, Mojito Potato Pomegranate Salad[/caption]

I had a great time hearing from the guests about their food blogs and other publications and it definitely made me want to go home and cook up a storm! Melissa's graciously gifted us with a box of fresh produce to try out some of Raghavan's recipes, which I'll use for our team lunch on Saturday. I'm sure Paris and Nyana will be thrilled!

[caption id="attachment_465" align="aligncenter" width="700"]<img class="wp-image-465" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/IMG_0013-1024x683.jpg" alt="Melissa's Produce and Raghavan Iyer" width="700" height="467" /> Photo Credit: Melissa's Produce[/caption]

Thank you to Melissa's and Raghavan for a really yummy afternoon!

Thanks for stopping by our blog and stay tuned for more fun news and marketing tips.

Photo credit: Knit Marketing unless otherwise noted.

-Rebecca

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>
</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Why Do You Need a Brand Design Guide? A guest blog post by Graphic Designer, Dorey Kronick</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/why-do-you-need-a-brand-design-guide-a-guest-blog-post-by-graphic-designer-dorey-kronick/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 16 Mar 2017 19:36:39 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=472</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">

<strong>Intro:</strong>

Branding can be challenging for any size company, and it comes up a lot in the work we do at Knit Marketing, because we're constantly asking our clients for logo files, what fonts they use, their specific colors, etc. We recently went through our own process of having our friend and graphic designer, <a href="http://doreykronick.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Dorey Kronick</a> help us put everything in one place for Knit in the form of a brand guide (or design guide), and we asked her to share a little more about why this is so critical for companies of all sizes and lifecycle stages.
<h1>Brand Guides</h1>
<h2><b><span style="font-size: large;"><i>A guest blog post by Graphic Designer, Dorey Kronick</i></span></b></h2>
BRAND GUIDES: They're more valuable than you realize.

...Why?

Let's say you're a new business owner &amp; you hire a graphic designer (like myself, <a href="http://doreykronick.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?hl=en&amp;q=http://doreykronick.com&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1489778947932000&amp;usg=AFQjCNErWOFp9mmCkUcjS3YPQmwIeM-c8A">Dorey Kronick</a> ;) ) to create a custom logo.
<div class="m_-9047845855680289597gmail-text_exposed_show">

Cool! Now you have a logo.

...What next?

Well, you still probably need a website, an email newsletter template, images to post on social media, business cards, &amp; other marketing collateral to start promoting your business &amp; driving in sales.

...But maybe you have no clear idea of how to create this stuff yourself, what fonts or colors will look good with your new logo, what mood / feel / style / vibe you're going for with these materials, or even where to start.

HHEEEYYYYOOOOO, that's where a <a href="http://doreykronick.com/design/#/brand-guides/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Brand Guide</a> comes in!

Truth be told, it's probably the safest idea to have the same graphic designer who created your logo also put together your Brand Guide. They're likely going to know your company's vision, mission, voice, &amp; goals better than anyone. And assuming they're a pro, they should be able to help you match the best fonts, colors, &amp; even photography styles to your new logo to create a smooth, professional, &amp; consistent look &amp; feel across the board for all of your company's materials.

Having a Brand Guide with this kind of information laid out in an organized &amp; understandable fashion from the start will help your company move forward with everything you need to put together for social media, e-mail marketing, websites, in-house materials, flyers, &amp; beyond! Potential customers &amp; fans will start to recognize the content you put out by becoming familiar with your overall brand &amp; identity - no matter where it is!

BUT maybe you're an established company who has been in business for years &amp; you already have a logo, (along with some other marketing materials that have carried you this far), &amp; you don't have a Brand Guide...

And maybe the time comes that you're ready to hire a company (like Knit ;) ) to start managing all of your marketing on Facebook, Instagram, Twitter, MailChimp, &amp; other places of the like... Hooray!

Well, let's say the marketing team you hired is starting next week, you've got big ideas in your head about all of the new customers that'll start lining up to support your business, &amp; everything is feeling good! Your new marketing team is just about ready to get to work, so they ask you for your company's Brand Guide to get a better understanding of who your company is &amp; what it's all about...

...But you don't have a Brand Guide.

So, the marketing team asks you a bunch of important questions like:

- What fonts do you use on your website?

- What is your company's vision, mission, &amp; goals?

- Can you provide your company's Pantone colors &amp; the HEX codes?

- What kinds of photography represents your brand's style?

- What companies are you inspired by?

...And so on.

...What now?

Well, you could scramble to look up all of this information in your various notebooks / e-mail inboxes / etc, send it to your new marketing team, &amp; hope you answered every question they asked as best as you could... Or you could sit the new marketing team down &amp; go over all of this info in a PowerPoint presentation that you put together as quickly as possible... Or you could make up some impromptu answers to most of their questions because you never really thought about that stuff anyway...

...OR you could just make everyone's life a lot easier &amp; put all of this information into one place that's easy to read &amp; share, &amp; never have to deal with this kind of situation again by investing in a Brand Guide :)

So, if you can, you should reach out to the original graphic designer who designed your company's logo &amp; ask them for help putting together a Brand Guide to match. Or if for any reason that's not an option, you should ask your new marketing team if they have a preferred graphic designer who can help you create a custom Brand Guide!

Your new marketing team should hopefully be able to recommend a great graphic designer. But if they can't, you can always resort to the internet for help too... ;) Either way, it's never too late (or too soon!) to get your hands on a Brand Guide. I've worked with companies who've literally had nothing - no logo, no colors, no fonts, no photos... To companies who have been around for quite a while &amp; had no set of Brand Guides. I've even worked with companies who have decided to switch everything up, start over, rebrand, &amp; put together a completely new, revised Brand Guide containing everything from a new logo to an entirely new look altogether!

<span style="color: #1d2129;">So until next time, check out the awesome Brand Guide I put together for Knit Marketing </span><span style="color: #1d2129;">after designing their custom company logo in 2016!<i> (See below.) </i></span><span style="color: #1d2129;">And for other fabulous Brand Guide samples, head over to my website at </span><a href="http://doreykronick.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?hl=en&amp;q=http://doreykronick.com&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1489778947932000&amp;usg=AFQjCNErWOFp9mmCkUcjS3YPQmwIeM-c8A"><span style="color: #0000ff;">http://doreykronick.com</span></a><span style="color: #1d2129;">! </span>

<img class="aligncenter wp-image-473" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/KNIT-BRAND-GUIDE-FOR-IG.jpg" alt="Knit Marketing Brand Guide" width="750" height="2244" />

<hr />

Thanks so much to Dorey for this awesome post and thanks to our readers for stopping by!

-#TeamKnit
<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>
</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Documenting History in Women&#039;s History Month</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/documenting-history-in-womens-history-month/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 28 Mar 2017 19:08:13 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=492</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h1>Documenting History in Women's History Month</h1>
As we wrap up Women's History Month, I wanted to take a moment to recognize the women that are making history as our first employees ever! We tend not to think of our current situation as "history," but in fact, it is. Paris and Nyana are building their own stories and contributing to the stories of Knit Marketing. We already can look back on the days of running around the USC campus, looking for the best quiet workspaces and all over LA looking for the best coffee shops as our temporary office space. In only 10 months, we feel like we've come pretty far.

It was not intentional to select only female interns when we started out, but they rose to the top and were excited to be part of the founding team. So before we let the busyness of running a startup get in the way, I wanted to reflect on our very own <em>women's history. </em><strong>
</strong>

<strong><img class="alignleft wp-image-497" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/IMG_0890-1-e1490725665561.jpg" alt="Paris Thomas Knit Marketing" width="250" height="333" />Paris Thomas </strong>is a senior in high school and wants to be a child forensics psychologist. She participates on her school's debate team, and has been identified as the "closer." Paris volunteers for more organizations and groups than I probably even know, but the ones I've heard her talk about are helping out middle schoolers in after school programs like iMentor Global, volunteering at a day care, and participating in student government. She also took an etiquette class last year, so she teaches us which fork we're supposed to use at restaurants, and how to eat very lady-like. Paris loves to travel and loves making arts and crafts. She's very entrepreneurial, as she has her own website where she sells repurposed and restored clothing items. She talks about her little sister more than anyone else and she takes her role as big sister very seriously. She has applied to several universities, has received acceptance letters from many, and is still waiting to hear back from her top choices. We're hoping she chooses UC Irvine, so she doesn't have to go too far (they also have some great courses on forensics, criminology, and social psychology that are right up Paris' alley). At Knit Marketing, Paris has been in charge of Twitter and Facebook until she recently took over a main account for one of our clients and will be managing their cohesive digital marketing strategy. She likes spicy food and loves her dad's Jamaican cooking. She likes to lip sync as she works, so I imagine her having full blown solo dance parties at home. If Paris stays with Knit Marketing, she definitely has a future in sales and consulting.

&nbsp;

[caption id="attachment_508" align="aligncenter" width="700"]<img class="wp-image-508" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/20161015_115215.jpg" alt="" width="700" height="394" /> Nyana and Paris when they finished their 12-week internship.[/caption]

&nbsp;

<strong><img class="wp-image-496 alignleft" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/IMG_0920-e1490725710810.jpg" alt="Nyana Slaughter Knit Marketing" width="250" height="333" />Nyana Slaughter</strong> is also a senior in high school and wants to be a Registered Nurse. She's been assigned the task of helping any sick or hurting family member since she was a little kid. She claims that blood and guts don't gross her out, but we tease her about being a bit of a germaphobe. If anyone in her life has to go to the hospital for any minor or severe problem, Nyana is always among the first to arrive. Nyana also works part time at a local grocery store, where she is picking up some Spanish words and learning a lot about customer service. She's made it pretty clear that working for Knit is a very "bougie" work experience in comparison, and I take that as a compliment. She used to play rugby, but decided to sit out this year to focus on work and college applications. She has received acceptance letters from most of the universities she applied to, is still waiting to hear back from a couple, and is still deciding among her top choices; one of which is Mount Saint Mary's for their nursing program. Nyana talks about her mom more than anyone else, and will most likely choose a school that is close to home so she doesn't have to leave her bestie (of course, I'm happy she'll be sticking around too!). At Knit, Nyana was in charge of Instagram and Pinterest, but also recently took over a main client account, for which she'll be managing their overall digital marketing strategies. She loves macaroni and cheese more than life itself, and especially if it's her mom's recipe. At work, we have to hide away in a closed conference room, because Nyana has a fabulous and infectious laugh, and we just don't want anyone to know how much fun we're having. If Nyana stays with Knit Marketing, she has a future in event planning and project management.

I am beyond blessed to have such a great founding team made of creative, fun, and brilliant young women. They teach me new things every week and challenge me to be a better leader, so we all continue to grow in this process. I hope they stick around for a long time, but even if they don't, I know Paris and Nyana will be making history wherever they go!

Thanks for reading our blog. We'd love to hear your thoughts, so be sure to drop us a line in the comments below.

-Rebecca | Founder

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank">Contact us</a> for more information. </em></div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Welcome to the Team Adewole Williams!</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/welcome-to-the-team-adewole-williams/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 08 Apr 2017 02:44:07 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=520</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h1>Welcome to the Team Adewole Williams!</h1>
At Knit, we haven't advertised the web development portion of our business very much, but it’s where we’ve seen a lot of growth and demand. Because we’re all about hiring young people, this has opened up a great opportunity for us to expand our team, so we are really excited to announce and welcome our newest team member, Adewole Williams!

Adewole will be helping with client projects and to build a bigger better Knit Marketing website. The whole team also sees a lot of potential in him training and leading future web developers.

<img class="alignleft wp-image-525 size-medium" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/LinkedIn-Profile-Picture-233x300.jpg" alt="Welcome to the Team Adewole WIlliams" width="233" height="300" />Adewole Williams is a 1st generation Nigerian, who graduated from the University of California: Riverside in 2013. Since high school, he’s been involved in different non-profits centered around youth and the environment. Adewole’s passion for technology and graphics led him to independently pursue gigs in graphics design while in college, and after. Currently working for the Los Angeles Conservation Corps, Adewole is deeply committed to improving disadvantaged communities through different state funded projects. During his down time he enjoys going on rides on his motorcycle, playing basketball, and creating music, and animations.

Welcome to the team!

Thanks for reading our blog! Stay tuned for more team updates, business news, and marketing tips.

-#TeamKnit

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Join #TeamKnit as a Summer Intern!</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/join-teamknit-as-a-summer-intern/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 02 May 2017 21:26:09 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=533</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h1>Join #TeamKnit as a Summer Intern!</h1>
It's already been a year since Knit Marketing began recruiting for our first summer interns and we are ready for round 2!

If you (or someone you know) are a teen looking for part-time summer work, interested in learning more about web marketing, now is your chance to apply to be a vital part of #TeamKnit!

<img class="size-large wp-image-538 aligncenter" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/summer-intern-no-blog-info-1024x1024.png" alt="" width="600" height="600" />

Please see below for the job description and to fill out an application.
<h2>Knit Marketing Job Description</h2>
<a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Knit-Marketing-Summer-Intern-Job-Description.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Download Job Description</a>

<strong>Job Title:</strong> Intern

<strong>Position Type:</strong> Part-time

<strong>Location:</strong> Los Angeles (Downtown and Santa Monica)

<strong>Date posted:</strong> May 1, 2017

<strong>Applications due: </strong>May 31, 2017

<strong>Hourly wage:</strong> $10.50

<strong>Role and Responsibilities</strong>
<ul>
 	<li>Learn about digital marketing – social media, email campaigns, blogs, influencer marketing, etc.</li>
 	<li>Research relevant content for Knit clients.</li>
 	<li>Plan and schedule social media posts.</li>
 	<li>Keep track of analytics and communications.</li>
 	<li>Learn how to plan and execute a digital marketing strategy.</li>
</ul>
<strong>Qualifications and Education Requirements</strong>
<ul>
 	<li>Must be at least 16-years-old.</li>
</ul>
<strong>Preferred Skills</strong>

Have general knowledge of the following, or be excited to learn:
<ul>
 	<li>Instagram, Facebook, and Twitter posts</li>
 	<li>Basic understanding of Microsoft Office and Google Docs</li>
</ul>
<strong>Time commitment</strong>
<ul>
 	<li>8-12 hours per week</li>
 	<li>The Knit team usually works on Saturdays and Sundays, but time can be flexible.</li>
</ul>
<strong>About Knit Marketing:</strong> Knit Marketing is a social enterprise that hires teens and young adults to manage social media, blog, and email campaigns for small to medium sized businesses. Knit Marketing also helps clients to create and maintain websites that are aligned with the companies’ marketing needs.
<h3><strong>To Apply</strong></h3>
<ol>
 	<li><strong>Fill out Application:</strong> <a href="https://goo.gl/forms/QvEBUcezc53mAjKF2">https://goo.gl/forms/QvEBUcezc53mAjKF2</a></li>
 	<li><strong>E-mail:</strong> <a href="mailto:Rebecca@knitmarketing.com">Rebecca@knitmarketing.com</a>
<ul>
 	<li>With subject line: Applying for Knit Marketing Summer Intern</li>
 	<li>Attach Cover Letter (resume is optional, but applications without a cover letter will not be considered)</li>
</ul>
</li>
 	<li><strong>Apply by May 31, 2017</strong></li>
</ol>
<a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Knit-Marketing-Summer-Intern-Job-Description.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Download Job Description</a>

</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Welcome to the Team Yesenia and Jorge!</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/welcome-to-the-team-yesenia-and-jorge/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 24 Jun 2017 04:05:14 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=544</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h1>Welcome to the Team Yesenia and Jorge!
(and other Knit news...)</h1>
<strong>The whole reason Knit Marketing exists is to be able hang out with cool teens like Yesenia and Jorge!</strong>

Each summer, we offer a 12-week internship that may lead to a part time position with Knit Marketing. This summer as we entered our 2nd year, we recruited through social media, various schools and organizations, and did an info session at Synergy Quantum Academy. We received over 20 applications from Synergy, Downtown Magnets High School, and even 1 from Berkeley, conducted 11 in-person interviews, and selected 2 interns. It was a difficult choice because all 11 interviewees were incredible and from the bottom of our hearts, we want to be able to offer them all jobs (and one day we will), but this summer we narrowed it down to Yesenia and Jorge.

They have already begun training and are excited, but seem a little overwhelmed with how much they'll have to achieve over the next 12 weeks. We don't mess around at Knit Marketing!

We are so happy to welcome Yesenia and Jorge to the team.

&nbsp;

<img class=" wp-image-546 alignleft" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/IMG_0794.jpg" alt="" width="258" height="344" /><strong>Y</strong><strong>esenia Gomez</strong>

<em>Graduated from Downtown Magnets High School and will be attending UCLA in the fall.</em>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">I believe life should be about trying new things whenever you can, keeping an open mind is always a useful asset in life. My future goals include becoming a marketing manager which makes Knit Marketing the perfect place for me to be working as an intern. Furthermore, something I really value is giving back to the community, like someone once said, “Being rich isn’t about how much you have, but rather how much you give.” I believe this goal of mine correlates with that of Knit Marketing because the company is all about helping the youth get connected meanwhile helping businesses </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">succeed, which indirectly is helping the consumer population.</span>

&nbsp;
<p style="text-align: right;"><img class="wp-image-547 alignright" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/IMG_0796.jpg" alt="" width="258" height="344" /><strong>Jorge Guevara</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>Entering senior year at Synergy Quantum Academy.</em></p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">As technology and social media become more of an integral part of our world, I believe being able to use both effectively is extremely important. That is why I would like to become a software engineer and become more experienced in the field. As a high school student I still have much to learn. The opportunity to join Knit Marketing perfectly aligned with my goals and hopefully will teach me a lot.</span></p>
&nbsp;

And for those of you who are wondering what's happening with <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/documenting-history-in-womens-history-month/"><strong>Paris and Nyana</strong></a> (because I know they've developed a bit of a fan club), Paris will be starting at UC Irvine in September and Nyana will be going to Cal State Dominguez Hills in August. Both of them will be with us through the summer (and hopefully stay through college) and have taken on more challenging roles on the business development side of Knit Marketing.

<strong>We have a great team</strong> now with Yesenia and Jorge in training, <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/welcome-to-the-team-adewole-williams/">Adewole</a> managing the overhaul of the Knit Marketing website, and Paris and Nyana helping Rebecca to turn Knit Marketing into the <em>21st-century-</em><em>west-coast-version-of-"Mad-Men." </em>(You'll have to ask Rebecca to tell you more about that...)

<span style="font-weight: 400;"><img class="size-full wp-image-548 aligncenter" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/2017-06-23_0001.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="1636" /></span>

Thanks for stopping by!

-#TeamKnit

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>]]></content:encoded>

		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h1>Now Introducing #MiniKnit - Digital Marketing Consulting Services</h1>
At Knit, we talk to many small business owners and entrepreneurs who are in a grey area of deciding whether to outsource their digital marketing efforts or keep them in-house. This can be a tough decision to make based on time available, skill level, budget, and more than anything - the interest to do the work.

For small teams with small budgets, we generally recommend keeping things in-house. This helps the startup define and develop their voice, test what works and doesn't work, and have more of a direct relationship with their customers.

For those teams, we've developed #MiniKnit - which is everything we do for our monthly clients, but in a one-day workshop customized for entrepreneurs and small businesses. We come to you! We'll do an in-depth analysis of your current marketing efforts and work with you to develop an executable plan that you and your team will be able to take over. We'll plan periodic check-in calls after the workshop to make sure the ship is still sailing in the right direction.

<img class="alignnone wp-image-588" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/IMG_0760-e1498325696178.jpg" alt="MiniKnit" width="240" height="180" /> <img class="alignnone wp-image-586" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/IMG_0766-e1498325650707.jpg" alt="MiniKnit" width="240" height="180" /> <img class="alignnone wp-image-587" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/IMG_0762-e1498325675683.jpg" alt="MiniKnit" width="240" height="180" />

<a style="font-size: 20px;" href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/go/info-sheet/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Download our Info Sheet to read more about our #MiniKnit services.</a>

Thanks for reading our blog. Shoot us an email or give us a call if you have any questions about our services or just want to chat!

-#TeamKnit

<hr />

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>The Ultimate Interview Guide: A guest blog post by Omnikron President Robin Borough</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/the-ultimate-interview-guide-a-guest-blog-post-by-omnikron-president-robin-borough/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 30 Jun 2017 19:54:14 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=598</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">

<strong>Intro:</strong>

If the name of our guest blogger sounds familiar, that's because Robin is Rebecca's mom! She also happens to be an expert in helping people land their dream jobs. Because Knit Marketing's mission is all about creating job opportunities, we asked her to share her wisdom to our team and any other young person looking to ace an interview. We've already been blessed by her business savvy and advice and hope you will benefit too. Enjoy!

<img class="size-large wp-image-604 aligncenter" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/bench-accounting-49026-1024x683.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" />
<h1>The Ultimate Interview Guide</h1>
<h2><em>A guest blog post by <a href="http://www.omnikron.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Omnikron</a> President, Robin Borough</em></h2>
<h3><span style="color: #8ec11a;"><em>You get one shot at a good interview… Here’s a surprisingly easy way to stand out amongst your competition:</em></span></h3>
I’ve coached thousands of high-qualified job applicants during my 30-year tenure of running recruiting companies and placing lots of smart people in great jobs. The job landscape, global economy, technology and workplace culture have changed significantly over the last thirty years. Nowadays, with immediate access to almost any information you could ever want, you’d think job candidates would be sufficiently prepared for their interviews. That’s what you’d think.

It’s baffles me every time prospective applicants come into my office, with brand new folios, fancy resumes and shiny shoes… everything looks good at the start, but when I ask my first interview question, “So… tell me, what do you know about my firm?,” at least 50% of these fine looking candidates have no clue what we do, or they give a weak answer that shows minimal preparation. Wow. [I usually find a way to politely end the interview within 15 minutes when this happens.]

Consequently, one of the easiest ways to ace your job interviews is to prepare. Research the company and the people you may meet. Scour the corporate website, look at employee profiles in <a href="http://www.linkedin.com">LinkedIn</a>, sign up for a free account at <a href="http://www.owler.com">Owler</a>, use <a href="http://www.glassdoor.com">GlassDoor</a> and even just “Googling” and using <a href="http://www.wikipedia.org">Wikipedia</a> will give you valuable info for your upcoming interviews. I recommend doing your homework 2-4 days in advance – definitely not while in the lobby waiting for your appointment!

Because this article is written for the loyal friends and fans of Knit Marketing, be sure to check out the prospective company’s social media sites: Twitter, Instagram, Facebook, etc. This will give you a great view of the company’s personality and brand following.

<strong>When preparing, here’s the type of information you should be looking for:</strong>
<ul>
 	<li>Organizational chart – learn the top executives names and study their backgrounds, prior companies and education. This tip is particularly funny to me because most people miss this step.</li>
 	<li>Mission of the company and also the mission of the division or department you’re applying to work for.</li>
 	<li>Products and services and how this company ranks compared to its competition.</li>
 	<li>Take a little broader view and gain some insight about the industry served by this company as well – is the industry growing, stagnate or shrinking?</li>
 	<li>Mission of the job you’re interviewing for.</li>
 	<li>Profiles of the people who will be interviewing you and also profiles of those who may hold similar jobs to the one you will be interviewing for.</li>
 	<li>If you can, purchase or try out the product or service before you interview</li>
</ul>
<img class="size-large wp-image-603 aligncenter" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/7-things-to-know-before-an-410x1024.png" alt="" width="410" height="1024" />

Research is an easy step that pays big dividends. It’s so easy, you may think, “That’s just common sense.” If that’s what you think, then you’ve got 50% of the equation. It does make a lot of sense, but, fortunately for you – it’s not that common!

Tell us about your interview experiences – either from an interviewee’s or an interviewer’s perspective. I know the team at Knit Marketing would love to hear from you and if you write something really witty – they may Tweet and Share your great advice!

Robin L. Borough

President,
Omnikron Systems, Inc.
<a href="http://www.Omnikron.com">www.Omnikron.com</a>

<hr />

Thanks so much to Robin for this helpful post and thanks to our readers for stopping by! Good luck in your next job interview!

-#TeamKnit
<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>What is the Deal with Email Marketing?</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/what-is-the-deal-with-email-marketing/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 05 Jul 2017 00:32:13 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=619</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">

<img class="size-large wp-image-624 aligncenter" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/fabian-irsara-92113-1024x683.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" />
<h1>What is the Deal with Email Marketing?</h1>
I'd be lying if I said I didn't cringe a little when clients ask us to help them with an email campaign.

Let me explain.

Many of us sit in our inboxes all day, so we know email is indeed an effective form of communication. However, we also sit in our inboxes deleting (or entirely ignoring) anything that makes us feel like someone is just out to get our money or annoy us. I'm not saying that email campaigns don't work, because that would be factually untrue, and we're not here to present #fakenews. In fact, at Knit we use email sparingly, but for us it has been an effective way to get people to read our blogs who wouldn't otherwise see them. See our latest email <a href="http://mailchi.mp/d312b7ebfeb4/news-from-knit-marketing?e=1809b9aa91" target="_blank" rel="noopener">newsletter</a>.

What I am saying, is that email is not a solution in and of itself. Some people talk about email as if it's going to miraculously save their business or magically grow their client base from 1 to 100, simply by pressing send on Wednesday at 11:00 a.m. and that's just not the way it works.

If you google "does email marketing work?" you'll quickly find that it is still a highly successful tool, which is encouraging but also confusing. <a href="https://www.campaignmonitor.com/blog/email-marketing/2016/01/70-email-marketing-stats-you-need-to-know/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Campaign Monitor</a> reports that email marketing can have up to a 4400% return on investment, but what does that even mean and how do you make it work like that? Let's not forget that there's a lot of science (and art and love) that goes into getting those results. It doesn't happen from sending 1 or 2 email newsletters to a new group of prospects or to a purchased list.

<a href="https://blog.kissmetrics.com/beginners-guide-email-marketing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Kissmetrics</a> has a great guide to email marketing and they address these many conflicting questions such as timing, frequency, and follow up. To further illustrate these points, we've developed a helpful flowchart to email marketing. (Pinning encouraged.)

<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-651" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Email-Marketing-Flowchart-1.png" alt="" width="1000" height="765" />

</div>
<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h3 style="text-align: center;"><strong><a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Email-Marketing-Flowchart.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Download the Flowchart</a> </strong></h3>
I suppose it's true that you may have said yes to one or two "hey, want to grab a drink?" requests on <a href="https://www.gotinder.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tinder</a> without having much of a conversation, but <em>usually</em> people need a little more warming up than that. We're not all ready to get in bed with the next <a href="https://www.jossandmain.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Joss &amp; Main</a> that sends us a pretty newsletter.

The number one rule to remember with email marketing and social media, or any other form of marketing for that matter is: <strong><span style="color: #ff3399;">it's about building a long-term relationship</span>.</strong> It's not about you selling stuff and them buying. Email marketing works when the customer already knows who you are and they're in the mood and the position to purchase. You may have to send them 100 emails before they ever click "add to cart," but if you annoy them or don't provide value, they may unsubscribe before they ever get to that point.

I hope we haven't completely scared you away from email campaigns, but instead provided a way to do them well. If you ever have questions about how to run a successful campaign, feel free to contact us.

Thanks for stopping by our blog!

Rebecca Borough | Knit Founder

<hr />

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>]]></content:encoded>

	</item>
	<item>
		<title>Design Thinking Workshop with Marina Terteryan</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/design-thinking-workshop-with-marina-terteryan/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 13 Jul 2017 07:04:20 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=655</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h1><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-669" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/IMG_1005-e1499929360891-1024x997.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="584" /></h1>
<h1>Design Thinking Workshop
with Marina Terteryan</h1>
On Saturday, July 1st, the creative, beautiful, knowledgeable and talented Marina Terteryan, founder of <a href="http://www.whyservicedesignthinking.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Why Service Design Thinking Podcast</a> and co-founder of <a href="https://www.thegoodprojects.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">the Good Projects</a>, lead us in a Design Thinking workshop at Cross Campus. We learned all about Human Centered Design and how it's essential for good business. Then we did a deep dive into our own marketing strategies using some Design Thinking methodologies.

Read more about our journey below.
<h3>What is Design Thinking?</h3>
<div class="page" title="Page 7">
<div class="section">
<div class="layoutArea">
<div class="column">
<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><span style="color: #8ec11a;"><strong><em>Human Centered Design is: optimizing an experience, service, or product by considering the user’s needs during all phases of the development lifecycle.</em></strong></span></p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
We learned about the Design Thinking Process, which starts with empathy and understanding the people you're trying to help. You then define the problem, ideate solutions, and then enter a cycle of prototyping and testing your solution, while always keeping the humans in mind. While it's similar to what's taught in business school - you have to get out of the building - Design Thinking places even more of an emphasis on the empathy piece. Whereas in b-school, you're sort of looking for people who have problems, because you're trying to come up with a solution, in Design Thinking you're meant to spend time with people, get to know them, and better understand their problems before offering solutions. So actually a little more like Peace Corps. ;)

<img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-657" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/For-Knit-Marketing-1024x575.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="337" />
<h3>Exercise 1: Buyer Personas</h3>
Marina led us in an exercise on developing a buyer persona, which was fun because some of the team already felt like experts, as this is a tool we use for our clients at Knit as well. The idea is to create a fictional persona that might be buying your product or service.

We made a fictional character based on one of our client's buyers. We had a good time coming up with a name, some personality characteristics, where our buyer hangs out, what he reads, what problem he's looking to solve, and even some objections that he might have with the product. For any business, this is a worthwhile exercise. Get your team in a room, think about your frequent buyers or callers and give them a buyer persona. This will help you be better prepared to answer their questions and meet their needs.
<h3>Exercise 2: The Happy Startup</h3>
Marina shared a cute and fun framework with us, called the Happy Startup. Marina did a great job guiding us in discussion and pulling out comments, opinions, and great ideas from everyone on the team. It was really great to hear everyone's thoughts, what they're excited about, and what moves them both in their personal lives and with Knit Marketing. Below, you get a sneak peak into our discussion.

<img class="aligncenter wp-image-660" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/download.png" alt="" width="600" height="350" />

<img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-662" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/IMG_0969-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="450" />

<img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-663" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/IMG_0973-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="450" />
<h3>Exercise 3: Mind Maps</h3>
Mind maps are an underestimated tool. We learned that it's not even the tool that makes them so powerful, but the people in the room. Marina had us list lots of different facets of Knit Marketing, and then from each category, we had to pull out more specific details. We focused on Knit Marketing success stories, and how to market ourselves.

It might seem strange that a marketing company would have to brainstorm about how to market itself, but we're always open to new ideas and it was fun to see what we could create together. The team came up with so many great ideas in just a short amount of time. Our eyes were open to where this little tool could lead us.

In fact, we've already used it since our workshop with Marina to plan out our content strategy!

<img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-665" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/IMG_0975-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="450" />

<img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-666" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/IMG_0978-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="450" />

We are beyond grateful to Marina for her time and excellent facilitation skills. We've all talked a lot about our workshop since, and will continue to use what we learned and put our new Design Thinking skills to use!

Thanks Marina!

And thank you for stopping by our blog!

#TeamKnit

<hr />

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Trendy Teens</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/trendy-teens/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 20 Jul 2017 02:32:15 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=674</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h3>Intro:</h3>
We're taking a break from our normal marketing and Knit news blogs to talk about teen trends. Paris introduces this topic below with the latest styles. And make sure to read all the way to the end, because we have a contest for you!

<img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-677" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/les-anderson-217735-1024x692.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="405" />
<h1>What Makes You A Trendy Teen?</h1>
<h2><em>The hottest in Fashion, Trends, and Everything teens love!
<span style="color: #ff3399;">By Paris Thomas</span></em></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">“Fashion repeats itself” said my mother, and she didn’t lie! I’ve noticed vintage from the 80s and 90s are super trendy at the moment - or maybe it never even went out of style? The brand name Vans is supporting this trend. All over social media platforms, teens can’t scroll without seeing a picture of cute trendy vintage Vans. The checkered ones are my personal fav! And not to forget, the ripped high waisted jeans and shorts are a go-to this summer for girls. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Girls girls girls! Who would’ve ever thought that after all my long nights doing sit-ups, one-piece swimsuits are trending??? </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Clothes aren't the only thing that came back! <em>Spiderman</em> did! We grew up watching <em>Spiderman.</em> I’ll never forget going to the movies and still watching it when I get home over and over again. I feel like <em>Spiderman</em> watched me grow up. I’m actually surprised the movie was in a movie theater rather than just on Hulu or Netflix, because in this era that’s what’s always trending. Teenagers nowadays rarely enjoy average TV Shows; it's all about "Orange Is The New Black" and "Pretty Little Liars," which we can both find on Netflix.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Also, of course with so many changes, as a teenager, there is always a different lingo for each era. I’m pretty sure my mom probably said something like "rad," but instead we say "clutch,” meaning, "that’s good." </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="color: #000000;">Just</span><strong> <span style="color: #ff3399;">REMEMBER</span></strong>: With so many things always changing for teens whether it be fashion, trends, shows or slang, it is important to be yourself and be great!</span>

-Paris Thomas

<hr />

What are your favorite #TeenTrends? <strong><a href="http://wshe.es/RAk8CCDq" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Enter our Instagram photo contest</a></strong> for a chance to win a $25 Amazon gift card!

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>]]></content:encoded>
