	<item>
		<title>Back to School study Tips</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/back-to-school-study-tips/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 08 Aug 2017 21:37:11 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=689</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h3>Intro:</h3>
With our high school and college students entering their fall semester's this month and next, Nyana wrote a little blog on how to get into the groove of studying! Good luck this year.

<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-690" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Screen-Shot-2017-08-08-at-2.34.09-PM.png" alt="" width="677" height="510" />
<h1><span style="font-weight: 400;">Back to School Study Tips </span></h1>
<h2><em><span style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="color: #000000;">Learning Your Studying Style</span>
</span></em><span style="color: #ff6600;"><em><span style="font-weight: 400;">by </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Nyana Slaughter</span></em></span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">School can be really hard at times... Especially, if you don’t study. How many times have you been at school and your teacher gives a pop up quiz? You get this shocked look on your face, because you know you did everything else except study last night. This has happened to me multiple times and I have had that same shocked look on my face. Until every night, I took 30 minutes to study. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">It became awesome... okay, I’m lying. I hated it with passion, but it truly helped me in the end. Those pop quizzes and tests became a little less challenging. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">A couple of times, I failed at the 30 minutes of study time. But that’s only because I didn't know what my studying style was. Well you're probably wondering what is a studying style?? Your personal studying style is when you figure out what is the best way for you to study. Just write out what you can and cannot do during studying. For example, for me study needs to include: </span>
<ul>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">No music </span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Yes food </span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">No TV</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Must be quiet </span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Writing what I’m studying five times or more </span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Using flash cards </span></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Now once you figure that all out, you are now ready to study! Some good ways to study are to use flashcards, write things out multiple times, put it in a picture, find multiple sources for what you learned and practice it in many ways. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">There are so many ways to study. Every individual has to find his or her own way.  </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">I hope this was helpful and good luck!</span>

<hr />

What are your favorite #TeenTrends? <strong><a href="http://wshe.es/RAk8CCDq" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Enter our Instagram photo contest</a></strong> for a chance to win a $25 Amazon gift card! Contest ends August 19th.

</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>TeamKnit On Assignment: Teens Exploring Technology</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/teamknit-on-assignment-teens-exploring-technology/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 17 Aug 2017 20:15:23 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=695</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h3>Intro:</h3>
#Teamknit took a break from the office and visited Teens Exploring Technology (TXT) Demo Day on August 5th. The TXT event took place at University of Southern California, and was AMAZING! TXT is a non- profit that trains young men of color/minorities in the field of technology and coding, with innovative projects and while teaching entrepreneurship and building a brotherhood. Would you believe that teens are really creating apps? Paris reports on the event below. Check out what the winning app was!
<h1><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-698" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/B2AAEB51-9272-46F7-A908-BFD6C10679A6-1024x684.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="401" /></h1>
<h1><span style="font-weight: 400;">Teens Exploring Technology Demo Day</span></h1>
<h2><em><span style="color: #ff00ff;">By Paris Thomas</span></em></h2>
My Co- Worker, Nyana and I attended the demo day. The purpose of the event was to show friends and family what the students had learned over their time in the <a href="http://exploringtech.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TxT program</a>. It was really heart warming for me to see so many diverse young boys and how technology has changed their life and helped build lifelong friendships. Over 6 apps were created! There was an opportunity for everyone to present their app to the judges and compete for prize money.

The first place winners were “The Duck”!

The duck is “An Al Duck that keeps track of who enters or exits a building/facility.”  This invention was just the cutest! From the looks of it, it makes going to work fun. Seriously, imagine instead of a lame clock-in punch card or Excel sheet, being able to communicate your

<img class=" wp-image-699 alignleft" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/IMG_1065-e1503000805571-683x1024.jpg" alt="" width="284" height="426" />

Even though they were the winning team, there were so many other great inventions that caught my eye like Magna Space. Magna Space “allows users to rent physical magna books from peers in the magna community.” Basically it’s like trading books, I love the idea and concept of this especially because reading is so underestimated nowadays.

We only got a brief inside peak of the work that Teens Exploring Technology is doing, and it was really fun and inspirational. Check them out <a href="http://exploringtech.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a> and support young men in the world that are making a change!

<hr />

<div>

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>
</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Congratulations to Knit Marketing Newest Employees</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/congratulations-to-knit-marketing-newest-employees/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 09 Sep 2017 21:40:08 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=704</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h3>Intro:</h3>
We wrapped up the summer with our 2nd round of interns becoming official #TeamKnit employees and to celebrate, we had a little graduation for them. Paris writes about it below.

<img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-708" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/IMG_0410-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="450" />
<h1>Congratulations to Knit Marketing Newest Employees</h1>
<h2><span style="color: #ff3399;"><em>by Paris Thomas</em></span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Congratulations to Knit Marketing’s newest employees, Jorge and Yesenia! They graduated from interns and became employees. During their internship, they were taught marketing skills, social media skills, time management and basic skills to succeed in the marketing world. Growth is beautiful, to see someone grow and mature like they did and to see the little things change is just amazing!</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;"><img class="alignleft wp-image-709 " src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/IMG_2697-e1506200796106.jpg" alt="" width="331" height="441" />In honor of Jorge and Yesenia completing their internship we had a mini graduation ceremony and I must say I am truly thrilled to have two new talented people on #TeamKnit! Their presentations at the graduation blew my mind. Jorge made a video-game-themed PowerPoint and Yesenia's presentation was a hand drawn video. I really enjoyed it and think everyone else at the graduation did too. Being able to watch them graduate also reminded me of my own growth, I was just like them last summer. I was just in their shoes - kind of shy and nervous, but Knit broke me out of my shell. Working for Knit tested me and so I was forced to pull out the best of me. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Read more about <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/what-yesenia-learned-through-her-knit-marketing-summer-internship/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Yesenia's presentation</a>.</strong></span>

<strong>Read more about <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/what-jorge-learned-during-his-knit-marketing-summer-internship/">Jorge's presentation</a>.</strong>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">I’m very happy for Jorge and Yesenia, I believe it’s safe to say they are very happy for themselves. In the words of Jorge, “He wants to work for Knit Marketing forever.”.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Well welcome to #TeamKnit!!!</span>

-Paris Thomas
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>View the live stream from the event:</strong>
<iframe style="border: none; overflow: hidden;" src="https://www.facebook.com/plugins/video.php?href=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FKnitMarketing%2Fvideos%2F1044054775697189%2F&amp;show_text=1&amp;width=560" width="auto" height="543" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p>


<hr />

<div>

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>
</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Tech Day</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/tech-day/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 23 Sep 2017 21:36:17 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=714</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h3>Intro:</h3>
In an effort to jump start Knit's own marketing, we took the team to <a href="https://techdayhq.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TechDay LA</a>. We had a great time talking to startup founders, job seekers, and lots of interesting techies! Paris writes more about our day below.
<h1><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-715" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/IMG_0506-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="450" />Tech Day</h1>
<h2><span style="color: #ff3399;"><em>by Paris Thomas</em></span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you didn’t see Knit Marketing at TechDay, well it was your loss! This was Knit Marketing’s first TechDay and I must say we had a blast! If you stopped by our table, you know we had yummy cookies, coffee gift cards, T-shirts and the coolest stickers. TechDay gave our youth team a chance to really express what Knit Marketing is about and show others what we have learned. Plus we also got to see many cool exhibits ourselves. It was really mind blowing to see what is going on in the world of technology. It truly brings sparks to my eyes, to see so many inventors and new products that were created here in Los Angeles or even coming to Los Angeles. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Also, if your fear is that TechDay is “too techy,” don’t be scared; it’s the complete opposite! It’s full of fun. There’s plenty of cool new things to try and also very friendly people. I mean you can never go wrong with friendly people, right? I learned new words, new forms of transportation, and many new things that are coming to LA, I must say I enjoyed this experience. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Lastly, I want to encourage everyone to check out our social media! During tech day we had a cool giveaway every hour… I know right how cool is that, every hour… We posted the winners of the game on our social media! Plus you never know what other giveaways we have coming up! So be sure to check us out. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Thanks TechDay LA. Team Knit Had A Blast!</span>

<hr />

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Interview Tips</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/interview-tips/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 02 Sep 2017 22:31:53 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=719</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Intro:</strong> </span></h3>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">At Knit, it's our mission to help young people succeed in careers and college. While we'd love to be able to offer every teenager in LA a job at Knit Marketing, we'll start by providing resources that will help regardless of where they end up. Earlier this summer, Robin Borough wrote a great <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/the-ultimate-interview-guide-a-guest-blog-post-by-omnikron-president-robin-borough/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">how-to blog about acing</a> an interview. The blog below was written by Yesenia, as she gives a first hand account of interview tips and why preparation is so important!
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-722" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot-2.png" alt="" width="591" height="332" /></span>
<h1>The Basic Interview Guide</h1>
<h2><span style="color: #ff6600;"><em>by Yesenia Gomez</em></span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Looking to prepare for an upcoming interview? As an Intern at Knit Marketing, I know how you feel. I had to attend an interview session, I was so nervous to go I was questioning if the job is even worth it! Then I thought, even if I don’t get the job, at least I will have interview experience. So then I went and I was asked things about myself I didn’t even know yet, that as a teenager gave me an existential crisis! If I did not take the time to prepare, I know I would not have gotten the job. So the following is how I prepared for my first job interview. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The first step to applying for my job was to submit a cover letter and an optional resume, first off make sure you have submitted all the required documents or else you might not even get the chance to interview! Once I submitted all the required documentation, I was given a list of dates to pick for an interview. So when should you schedule your interview? To this I say pick the date not only based on days you are 100% sure you can make it, but base it on how you know yourself. Let’s take myself for example: I know if I give myself more time, I will procrastinate the researching and practicing part, so because of this I chose the very first date available to keep me under pressure. I also know I’m a morning person who thinks best earlier in the day, so I also chose the earliest time possible. To add on to this scheduling tip, any time you apply for a job constantly check your email, keep refreshing for any updates. It’s always best to answer emails as quickly as possible to guarantee your spot. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;"><img class="size-full wp-image-723 alignleft" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot-5.png" alt="" width="353" height="353" />So now you have scheduled your interview, whats next? RESEARCH. The night before my interview I spent about 2 hours researching tips, but one thing I lacked was confidence; during your interview don’t be afraid to make eye contact or to brag a little. As the timid person I am I had trouble expressing why I thought I was fit for the job, but don’t be afraid to say your good qualities and do your best to answer each question. If you look up potential questions you may be asked you will be highly relieved (keep in mind these may change based on the job you’re applying for). In my case, I researched interview questions for a marketing job. Once you find some good questions I recommend writing down any ideas that you could talk about. Rather than memorizing a script for each question, be flexible and just brainstorm ideas that you can talk about that way you can extend these ideas to other questions you may be asked. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">I know companies may sometimes cyberstalk possible employees, so after you do research on the possible questions, it’s your turn to cyberstalk the company! Make sure you are familiar with the company you are planning to work for. Look for their company mission statements, what they do and their visions. Once you feel you know enough you should think of ways to align your question replies to fit what the company wants or just likes. Also, after doing the company research you should come up with effective questions you could ask after the interview to let the company know you care and put thought into it. After all this, don’t over practice to the point where it’s no longer natural. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Now it’s time for your interview! Set at least 2 alarms to make sure you’re on time and give a good first impression. Make sure to dress nice, take time to plan your outfit the night before in case something in the morning does not go as planned. Once you get there don’t forget a firm handshake and don’t get nervous, show maturity and speak with confidence.  </span>

(P.S. Yesenia didn't mention that she was also the only interviewee to send a follow-up thank you email! This goes a long way in an interview, so don't forget this simple step. -Rebecca)

<hr />

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>]]></content:encoded>

			<wp:comment_date><![CDATA[2018-03-27 18:18:39]]></wp:comment_date>
			<wp:comment_date_gmt><![CDATA[2018-03-28 01:18:39]]></wp:comment_date_gmt>
			<wp:comment_content><![CDATA[Где провести время, как отметить торжество? 
Рекомендую проверенные кейтеринговые компании в Санкт-Петербурге. 
Что такое кейтеринговая компания? 
Это компания, которая занимается выездным ресторанным обслуживанием. 
Например если вы хотите отметить торжество, но вам не хочется самому, 
возиться с доставкой, подбором продуктов, посуды, мебели. Готовить самому, закупать продукты, 
да и отметить хочется не просто дома, а, например где-нибудь за городом. 
Во дворце, на теплоходе. Даже на крыше в старом Петербурге. 
Устроют регистрацию брака на выезд. 
Вопосов нет. 
Заказываете нормальный кейтеринг, вам предоставят всё и, потом, даже уберут посуду. ;-) 
Думаете это дорого? 
А вот и нет. 
Если подсчитать все хлопоты и подбор места для, например барбекю, забегаетесь… 
Подбор посуды, мебели и прочего такого удовольствия… 
Вызовите настоящего профессионала ресторанного дела, он вам оформит и сделает всё в лучшем виде. 
Всё накатано, отработано. 
Если нужно вызовет конферансье, музыкантом. 
Сыграет свадьбу, банкет, фуршет, барбекю за городом, на теплоходе на крыше и, 
вообще насколько развернётся ваша фонтазия, а может быть он предложит то, на что вы сами не нафантазируете. 
 
Да, кстати, если вы не хотите тратиться на телефонный звонок, 
оставьте в заявке свой телефон и вам позвонят. 
 
<a href="http://interfood-catering.ru" rel="nofollow">Кейтеринг в Санкт-Петербурге</a> 
<a href="http://premium-catering.ru/" rel="nofollow">Кейтеринг в Санкт-Петербурге</a>]]></wp:comment_content>

	<item>
		<title>Starting a Business</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/starting-a-business/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 16 Sep 2017 23:07:05 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=725</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h3>Intro:</h3>
Well, starting a business is definitely a difficult task that. And you're probably going to lose a bit of your hair, but in the end you’ll have something that you can be proud of.

Jorge and one of his friends are in the process of starting a T-Shirt design company, so he wanted to document everything he learned about starting a business. He also interviewed Anastasia Butler from <a href="http://sustainable-lawyer.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Sustainable Law Group</a> to get some pointers. Thanks Anastasia!

<img class="wp-image-729 size-large aligncenter" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/business_entities_labi-1024x575.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="337" />

&nbsp;
<h1>Starting your Business</h1>
<h2><span style="color: #0066ff;"><em>by Jorge Guevara</em></span></h2>
&nbsp;

<b>What is your purpose?</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">What purpose does your business serve? Knowing what problem your business is solving is crucial to its success. You have to know whether or not people are willing to pay for your product or service. Ask around and see if the people around you think your idea is reasonable. By no means should you quit if everyone tells you it's a bad idea, but it is important to take into account others' opinions as well.</span>

&nbsp;

<b>What kind of company are you? </b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The many companies that exist in the world are the ones that are allowed to exist by the consumers. There are a few company types out there and you have the pick of the litter...company type wise. If you are just starting out, then you are most likely going to be a sole proprietor or LLC. Sadly there are no cats involved. Use this tool from the SBA to get you to a place where enlightenment can be found. Come back once you understand. </span>

<a href="https://www.sba.gov/starting-business/choose-your-business-structure"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://www.sba.gov/starting-business/choose-your-business-structure</span></a>

&nbsp;

<b>What's your name again?</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Yeah, you have to make official. It’s the only way to really make it yours. You will have to get registered at your nearby registration office. But I wouldn’t recommend trying to call yourself Nike... I think it’s taken. </span>

<a href="https://www.sba.gov/starting-business/choose-register-your-business"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://www.sba.gov/starting-business/choose-register-your-business</span></a>

&nbsp;

<b>What do you need?</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Now that you know what it is that you are doing make a list of all the things your company is going to need. This includes items needed to make your product, a website, or things needed to make your company great. Like a sweet new suit(or dress)... well maybe once your company kicks off a bit.</span>

&nbsp;

<b>Make a website/ start your social media</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">If you’re not online, you’re not anywhere. In fact you are reading this on our very own website. Having a presence online is crucial to getting your message to other people. Especially because other forms of media no longer work like they used to. </span>

&nbsp;

<b>Find your market</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Look at who it is you're selling your product or service to. This is crucial for knowing where to position yourself. Once you know who your client is, then you know where to focus your efforts. Customer discovery is one of the most important steps in creating a successful business. It allows you to know if the people you plan on selling to even want what it is that you offer. If they don’t, then you’ll probably want to find a new market or consider changing your idea into something that people are looking for or want.</span>

&nbsp;

<b>Get some partners</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The road to success can be lonely, so find yourself some willing individuals who have faith in your company. People whose goals align with yours are perfect candidates. Not only this, but letting other people take some of the work can help you from getting exhausted with all your work.</span>

<hr />

<div>

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>
</div>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>What Yesenia Learned Through her Knit Marketing Summer Internship</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/what-yesenia-learned-through-her-knit-marketing-summer-internship/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 28 Sep 2017 01:30:39 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=750</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h3>Intro:</h3>
On September 2nd, we hosted a graduation for our summer interns. They were tasked with presenting a summary of what they learned through their 12-week internship with Knit Marketing.

Yesenia shared this video that she created, drew, and narrated telling the story of her summer with Knit. Our guests were blown away by her talent and our team was touched by how much the experience of working with Knit meant to Yesenia. Enjoy and feel free to share!
<h1>What Yesenia Learned Through her Knit Marketing Summer Internship</h1>
<h2><span style="color: #ff3399;"><em>By Yesenia Gomez</em></span></h2>
<p style="text-align: center;"><iframe style="border: none; overflow: hidden;" src="https://www.facebook.com/plugins/video.php?href=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FKnitMarketing%2Fvideos%2F1046257725476894%2F&amp;show_text=0&amp;width=560" width="800" height="450" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" data-show-captions="true"></iframe></p>
Thanks for watching! We streamed the whole graduation, which you can see on our <a href="https://www.facebook.com/KnitMarketing/videos/vb.685086701594000/1044054775697189/?type=2&amp;theater" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Facebook page.</a>

<strong>See more about our intern graduation <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/congratulations-to-knit-marketing-newest-employees/">here</a>. </strong>

See you soon!

<hr />

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>What Jorge Learned During his Knit Marketing Summer Internship</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/what-jorge-learned-during-his-knit-marketing-summer-internship/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 02 Oct 2017 23:38:14 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=758</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h3>Intro:</h3>
On September 2nd, we hosted a graduation for our summer interns. They were tasked with presenting a summary of what they learned through their 12-week internship with Knit Marketing.

Jorge put together a very creative presentation in the theme of a Nintendo video game which jumped to a "new world" at the end of each lesson. He shared both things he learned about social media and analytics, but also the life lessons learned. Such as being prepared, the benefit of having an outside perspective, and many more great lessons. See his slides below to venture into his internship world!
<h1>What Jorge Learned During his Knit Marketing Summer Internship</h1>
<h2><span style="color: #0066ff;"><em>By Jorge Guevara</em></span></h2>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-761" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Tutorial.jpg" alt="" width="960" height="540" />

<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-759" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/World-1.jpg" alt="" width="960" height="540" />

<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-760" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/World-2.jpg" alt="" width="960" height="540" />

<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-762" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Final-Boss.jpg" alt="" width="960" height="540" />

Thanks for stopping by! We streamed the whole graduation, which you can see on our <a href="https://www.facebook.com/KnitMarketing/videos/vb.685086701594000/1044054775697189/?type=2&amp;theater" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Facebook page.</a>

<strong>See more about our intern graduation <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/congratulations-to-knit-marketing-newest-employees/">here</a>. </strong>

See you soon!

<hr />

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

	<item>
		<title>You Might Be Small But Culture Wins Big</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/you-might-be-small-but-culture-wins-big/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 30 Oct 2017 17:51:10 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=776</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h3>Intro:</h3>
Over the summer, we had the pleasure of welcoming Adam and Allen from <a href="http://www.bourbonfat.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bourbon Fat</a> to facilitate an employee experience workshop for our team, that they creatively retitled “Employee Experience <strong>FRAPPY</strong> Hour.” Because the majority of our team members are under 21, Frappuccinos seemed a little more fitting than cocktails. Bourbon Fat led us through several exercises including writing, drawing, prototyping, and acting, that allowed everyone on the team to openly share about their hopes, challenges, and preferences when it comes to work. Read our blog on their website <a href="http://www.bourbonfat.com/speakeasy/2017/8/31/company-culture-in-a-small-team" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.

In today's blog Allen and Adam share their wisdom on company culture.

[caption id="attachment_780" align="aligncenter" width="800"]<img class="size-full wp-image-780" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/IMG_8564.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="533" /> Photo Credit: Eric Garvey[/caption]
<h1>You Might be Small but Culture Wins Big</h1>
<h2><span style="color: #0066ff;"><em>By Allen Weaver &amp; Adam Allred, Co-Founders of Bourbon Fat</em></span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">There’s a lot of stress in launching your own small business. From deciding whether you’re an LLC or an S-Corp to identifying your customer niche to marketing to hiring employees, it can be overwhelming. It’s also certainly easy enough to get lost in the land of administrative hell. As bills start coming in, and as clients start to grow (along with their level of expectations), it is easy to forget about why you’ve started a business to begin with, as well as forgetting about the well-being of those you’ve hired to help you.</span>
<h3><span style="color: #8ec110;">The Culture Chasm</span></h3>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">While your team of employees might initially be motivated and enthused for the adventure of starting a brand-new company from the ground up, they eventually fall into what’s referred to as the “cultural chasm.” David Niu, the CEO of TINYpulse, and Mark Roberge, the Chief Revenue Officer of HubSpot, </span><a href="https://hbr.org/2017/03/how-morale-changes-as-a-startup-grows"><span style="font-weight: 400;">define</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> the cultural chasm as, “the rough patch for about 70% of startups in years three to four regardless of how happy the team was before.” How do they explain this shift in startup culture? Well, as you can imagine, if you’re the founder of a new company focused on surviving and making a profit, you’re likely growing blind to the cultural well-being of the company at the expense of the Employee Experience and employee engagement. </span>

[caption id="attachment_781" align="alignleft" width="400"]<img class="wp-image-781" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/IMG_8416.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="267" /> Photo Credit: Eric Garvey[/caption]

<span style="font-weight: 400;">According to Niu and Roberge, not valuing the cultural stability of your company beyond the excitement of launch and when the coolness of fun office perks wears off, you’re looking at having a 70% chance of higher employee turnover than startups who remain focused on the importance of culture. Maybe you think turnover isn’t that big of a deal when you’re first starting out. Well, consider this. In 2016, the Society for Human Resource Management (SHRM) estimated the average time to hire a new employee is 42 days at a cost of $4,192. Let’s say you have 10 employees. If 7 of them quit throughout the year due to burnout or not feeling heard, you’d be looking at 294 lost days of work impacting your efficiency, not to mention decreasing the remaining employees’ morale. In addition, you’d spend about $29,344 to replace those employees and that’s only accounting for the basics. This number is much larger depending on the scope and scale of the position you’re hiring for plus the hours lost for how many other people are involved in the search.</span>
<h3><span style="color: #8ec110;">Bridging the Chasm</span></h3>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">We advise you to take some of that money you’d potentially lose through turnover and invest it back into your employees through incentives, wellness and development opportunities, team building, and additional resources. Don’t forget to throw in some happy hours of course! Even after all of that, you’d likely spend far less money than the cost and time to replace employees. Plus, your team would remain highly engaged resulting in only good things for your business and customers.</span>
<h3><span style="color: #8ec110;">How to Recognize if You’re Falling into the Chasm</span></h3>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">At Bourbon Fat, we’re currently developing a fun diagnostic for leaders and HR teams to gauge how their employees are feeling about the company culture and their Employee Experience. We’ll give you sneak peek of that below, but there’s a DIY approach you can take for now.</span>

[caption id="attachment_784" align="alignright" width="400"]<img class="wp-image-784" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/IMG_8504.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="267" /> Photo Credit: Eric Garvey[/caption]

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Good ole-fashioned listening and transparent communication is a great way to get started on your own. Take </span>intentional pauses during your crazy startup journey to sit and chat with your employees about how they are feeling, where they see inefficiencies, and what ideas they have for their own growth and development. The more you can illustrate their career path options expanding as the company grows, the better! You can also share with employees the challenges you are personally facing along with the company’s long-term obstacles. Then, ask them for their input to solving those challenges! Framing work that still needs to be accomplished as challenges rather than dictating them as assignments, makes the team feel valued and empowered as problem solvers.

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Having a sense of meaning in work, opportunities to create connections with coworkers, and access to leadership and resources makes for a top-shelf </span><a href="http://www.bourbonfat.com/speakeasy/2017/5/29/the-ingredients-for-crafting-the-perfect-employee-experience"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Employee Experience</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and overall company culture. All of these ingredients stirred together lead to more engaged employees.</span>
<h3><strong><i><img class=" wp-image-783 alignleft" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/dive_cards_sample-300x279.png" alt="" width="258" height="240" /></i></strong><span style="color: #8ec110;">A Sneak Peek at DIVE</span></h3>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">We mentioned above that we’re working on a diagnostic as well as an accompanying toolkit to help leaders and HR teams assess and creatively improve their company culture and Employee Experience. Here’s a look at what you’ll find in our DIVE card sort diagnostic. Once we finish testing and refining, we’ll look to launch in 2018.</span>

<hr />

<strong><a href="http://www.bourbonfat.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="size-medium wp-image-788 alignleft" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/IMG_9818-300x200.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="200" /></a></strong><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-797" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/BF_TYPE_BLK200px-300x31.png" alt="" width="300" height="31" />
<strong><a href="http://www.bourbonfat.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bourbon Fat</a> designs meaningful employee experiences</strong>.

Follow them on social media:

<a href="https://www.facebook.com/bourbonfat" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://www.facebook.com/bourbonfat</a>
<a href="https://twitter.com/BourbonFat" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://twitter.com/BourbonFat</a>
<a href="https://www.instagram.com/bourbonfat1920" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://www.instagram.com/bourbonfat1920</a>

	<item>
		<title>Join that School Extracurricular!</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/join-that-school-extracurricular/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 07 Nov 2017 02:44:41 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=805</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h3>Intro:</h3>
As a few of our team members started their Freshmen year in college, we thought it was only appropriate to share some back to school wisdom - for high school and college students. Here, Yesenia shares all about the extracurriculars that make going to school so much more worth it.

</div>
<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">

<img class="size-full wp-image-806" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/ODUD8X0-e1510022501594.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="528" />
<h1>Join that School Extracurricular!</h1>
<h2><span style="color: #ff00ff;"><em>By Yesenia Gomez</em></span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">From personal experience, I can say extracurriculars play a big part of school life. In high school, I was involved in many clubs and sports teams and I regret not joining all of them earlier! Many people encourage extracurriculars simply to have your college application look more full. While that is true, there is a lot more to participating in extracurricular activities. I personally found the benefits of these activities to be beyond measure. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Just to lay out some examples, sophomore year of high school I found myself joining the cross country and track teams. Let's say these teams taught me a lot, from fun to life tips, I learned it all. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Why not start off with the fun part? Being in these teams meant I got to make a lot of friends (who were by the way, each amazing people with different passions and views but we all connected through running). Each day after school at practice was a new experience, a new laugh, we made amazing memories with one another, from getting injured to potlucks. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Running taught me a lot about what I can handle, through the worst moments I always finished my races, I learned keeping a calm and positive mind is what gets you through these moments! During my first marathon, I remember feeling like quitting, but the fighter in me kept running and just smiling through the pain with my teammates next to me.  If it weren’t for me joining these teams I would have never got all these great memories! </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">But enough with the cheesy stuff, I also got the opportunity to be the president of CSF an academic organization. Being in this position really taught me about leadership, I learned to come out of my shy shell and lead a group of 60 something members. I learned to be organized, to plan meetings, and lots of team work with my cabinet. Furthermore, I made plenty of connections, I got the awesome opportunity to work with other organizations to run a service fair! I got to work with amazing teachers who continued to show their support and help me with things not just involving the club. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Having to run this club and run, literally, for the sports teams I was in, along with having after school classes everyday and other clubs like the newspaper team was really tough but really worth it. I became a well-rounded person, the person I am today, because of these activities, I got into a good college too! </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Best of all, they gave me a boost during an interview to be a part of the best team in the world, #TeamKnit! Share your extracurricular activities and encourage others to be a part of these amazing activities!</span>

<hr />

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>GET STUFF DONE Conference Speakers</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/get-stuff-done-conference-speakers/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 07 Nov 2017 04:57:45 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=808</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h3>Intro:</h3>
On December 9th, Knit Marketing will be hosting the GET STUFF DONE Digital Marketing Conference! We are excited to welcome the following incredible Speakers and Facilitators. Check back often, as we'll be updating this page before the event!

<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-819" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/GET-STUFF-DONE-Digital-Marketing-Conference-e1510071392753.png" alt="" width="800" height="486" />

</div>
<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h1>Introducing our <a href="https://knit-getstuffdone.eventbrite.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GET STUFF DONE</a> Conference Speakers and Partners:</h1>
&nbsp;
<h3><a href="http://www.sozango.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">SoZango Solutions</a><a href="http://www.sozango.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="alignleft wp-image-809" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/sozango.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="155" /></a></h3>
SoZango designs chatbot solutions for high impact organizations. We deploy artificial intelligence (A.I.) to enable intelligence augmentation (I.A.) -- removing repetition from your job and promoting meaningful connections. We guide brands to discover what outcomes they are seeking, create a targeted content framework, and utilize the latest tech to craft a curated solution.

<em>Talk to us about conversations SO worth having <a href="https://www.facebook.com/SoZangoSolutions/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@sozangosolutions</a>.</em>

&nbsp;
<h3><a href="https://www.pitchgenius.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Jasmine Foroutan | Pitch Genius</a><a href="https://www.pitchgenius.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="alignleft wp-image-810" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Pitch-Genius-8712.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="231" /></a></h3>
Jasmine Foroutan is a full-time pitch deck specialist for tech startups, investors, and accelerators. She’s the Founder &amp; CEO of Pitch Genius, a boutique pitch deck consulting firm on a mission to help more startups get funded. The firm is based in Los Angeles, but has also helped startups successfully pitch in San Francisco &amp; New York.  She started her career in 2014 and holds a Bachelors in Entrepreneurship from Loyola Marymount University.

<em>Follow Jasmine on </em><a href="https://medium.com/@PitchGenius_Co" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Medium</em></a><em> and <a href="http://www.twitter.com/pitchgenius_co" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Twitter</a>, connect on </em><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jasmine-foroutan/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>LinkedIn</em></a><em>, and learn about pitch deck services at </em><a href="http://www.pitchgenius.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>www.pitchgenius.co</em></a><em>. Feel free to email her <a href="mailto:jasmine@pitchgenius.co">here</a>.  </em>

&nbsp;
<h3><img class="wp-image-812 alignleft" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/alex-6.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="200" /><a href="http://www.alecaddd.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Alessandro Castellani | Alecaddd</a></h3>
Alessandro, is a software developer from Italy who moved to Canada in 2014, mostly because he was tired of eating pizza and pasta every day. Currently working as Lead Developer and Product Manager at Ritual Music, he's a huge Open Source advocate, actively contributing to multiple Linux distros, sharing the source code of his projects, and developing native Open Source Linux applications. Mostly known online for his YouTube Channel, where he releases weekly tutorials about development and design.

<em>Follow Alex on <a href="https://www.youtube.com/user/williamprey" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YouTube</a> and <a href="https://twitter.com/alecaddd" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Twitter</a>, and connect with him on <a href="https://www.facebook.com/alecadddpage" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Facebook</a>. </em>

&nbsp;
<h3><img class="alignleft wp-image-816 size-full" style="font-size: 16px;" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/1888736_10151972729273652_482432480_n.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="200" /><a href="http://www.omnikron.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Robin Borough | Omnikron</a></h3>
As President of Omnikron Systems, Inc., Robin Borough has worked with scores of Fortune 100-500 companies, focusing on technology-related training and staffing solutions in areas including Big Data, Cyber Security, Cloud and Convergence, Process Transformation, Design Thinking and many other critical areas affecting today’s organizations.

Ms. Borough is the creator of the Learning Lifecycle™ and Leadership Elevation Framework™; she’s the CoFounder of <a href="https://thinkers50ecademy.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Thinkers50 eCademy</a> and board member for Thinking Dimensions Global. Ms. Borough is the author of the career management book, Competing for your Future; she often speaks on Career Acceleration and leads “Genius-on-Demand” workshops. Educated at California State University Northridge and Universite Laval, Ms. Borough lives in Southern California, is married with 5 adult children and a grand-baby on the way!

<em>Connect with Robin on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/robinborough/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a> or email her <a href="mailto:Robin.Borough@Omnikron.com">here</a>. </em>

&nbsp;
<h3><img class="wp-image-834 alignleft" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/headshot-yolanda-enoch-1.png" alt="" width="200" height="200" /><a href="http://www.yolandaenoch.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Yolanda Enoch</a></h3>
Yolanda Enoch is a multi-hyphenate who moved to Los Angles four years ago. She helps individuals organize their home and digital lives. So they can spend their mental resources on the things they actually care about.

She also hosts, produces, and edits the podcast How She Did It. The podcast explores the often winding and rarely linear career paths of women of color. The mission is to get more women of color to take action towards having a career they love.

Her career began in Human Resources in 2003. She uses that experience to provide recruiting and HR operations support to companies.

<em>Connect with Yolanda on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/yolandaenoch" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>, email here <a href="mailto:hi@yolandaenoch.com">here</a>, or follow her on Instagram, Twitter, and Facebook at @yolandaenoch.</em>

&nbsp;
<h3><img class="wp-image-839 alignleft" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/GWxzdrXH1O9AZBQSAqnEUc4IZ3-zrDQchNHFGjK3VOE.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="183" /><a href="http://somethingsocial-la.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Marissa Stahl | Something Social</a></h3>
Marissa Stahl is the Vice President of Operations at Something Social, a Digital Media &amp; Creative agency located in Los Angeles, CA. Having worked with over 65+ brands, her expertise lies in translating a brand’s mission &amp; purpose into a visual portrayal and executing it in the digital space. Well versed in the inner-workings of all social media platforms, she is your go-to for social media &amp; digital strategy. Marissa is a graduate of the University of Southern California.

<em>Email Marissa <a href="mailto:marissa@somethingsocial-la.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a> and follow her on Instagram and Twitter @marissacstahl. </em>

&nbsp;
<h3><img class="wp-image-837 alignleft" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/i-Zqn7Qw6-XL-e1511216214271.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="214" /><a href="http://xavierdipetta.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Xavier Di Petta</a></h3>
Xavier is an 21-year-old serial entrepreneur from rural Australia who made the big move to California. In 2014, as a senior in high school, Xavier and his co-founders raised 2 million dollars from several investors, including Upfront Ventures and 500 Startups, to build All Day Media. All Day is a digital media company that shares news and media content with the world through images.

More recently, Xavier has focused his energy of working with SMBs to grow their audience and generate leads using Facebook &amp; Instagram Ads.

Xavier began working with digital media at 11, uploading comedy skits on YouTube, and then moving onto use platforms that were up and coming at that time, such as Facebook and Twitter. He was attracted to social media because of its power to give ordinary people the ability to spread their messages across the world instantly.

<em>Email Xavier <a href="mailto:xavier@xavierdipetta.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>. </em>

&nbsp;

<hr />

<h3><strong>Stay tuned for more speaker updates. Buy a ticket to the conference <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/get-stuff-done-digital-marketing-strategy-conference-tickets-39295635303" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>. </strong></h3>

		<title>Get Stuff Done: Taking Plans from Paper to Action</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/get-stuff-done-taking-plans-from-paper-to-action/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 14 Nov 2017 17:50:33 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=830</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">

Press Release first seen on <a href="https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/get-stuff-done-taking-plans-from-paper-to-action-300555037.html" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">PRNewsire</a>
<h1>Get Stuff Done: Taking Plans from Paper to Action</h1>
LOS ANGELES, Nov. 14, 2017 /PRNewswire/ -- Knit Marketing, a team of diverse digital media experts, presents its first digital marketing conference, "Get Stuff Done." This one-day conference will give marketers, entrepreneurs, and startup founders the tools to turn ideas into executable marketing plans.

<strong>For Additional Details and Conference Registration, Click Here: </strong><a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/get-stuff-done-digital-marketing-strategy-conference-tickets-39295635303?aff=pr" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">https://www.eventbrite.com/e/get-stuff-done-digital-marketing-strategy-conference-tickets-39295635303?aff=pr</a>

On December 9th, attendees will meet the Knit team at the Downtown Los Angeles Cross Campus. Knit, which offers marketing consulting services to startups, will offer the same hands-on support to help attendees create innovative marketing solutions for their organizations.

On December 9th, attendees will meet the Knit team at the Downtown Los Angeles Cross Campus. Knit, which offers marketing consulting services to startups, will offer the same hands-on support to help attendees create innovative marketing solutions for their organizations.

SoZango, a rapidly growing chatbot company, says Knit Marketing "prompted us to think critically about our online presence. They're highly skilled not only in all things social media, but also in connecting the social to broader business initiatives. We have loved working with Knit and recommend them to any business, especially those looking to target young people!"

At the <a href="https://knit-getstuffdone.eventbrite.com/?aff=pr" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">"Get Stuff Done" conference</a>, guests will dive into hands-on breakout sessions about
<ul>
 	<li>Building a YouTube presence with YouTube expert Alessandro Castellani.</li>
 	<li>Perfecting a brand story with pitch deck specialist Jasmine Foroutan.</li>
 	<li>Utilizing AI (artificial intelligence) and chatbots to create unique and personalized conversations with customers with SoZango.</li>
 	<li>Featuring webinars as a lead generation and customer nurturing tool with marketing wizard Robin Borough.</li>
 	<li>Creating compelling and analytics-driven Facebook and Instagram ad campaigns with social marketing strategist Marissa Stahl.</li>
 	<li>Developing and promoting a podcast with organizational coach Yolanda Enoch.</li>
</ul>
Also, to highlight Knit's social mission of empowering youth, attendees will hear business pitches from the Network for Teaching Entrepreneurship (NFTE) Los Angeles alumni. In addition to networking with startup founders and corporate marketing teams, participants will walk away with a blueprint for their organizations' 2018 digital marketing strategy!

<strong>Tickets and more information</strong> are available at <a href="https://knit-getstuffdone.eventbrite.com/?aff=pr" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">https://knit-getstuffdone.eventbrite.com/?aff=pr</a>.

About <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">Knit Marketing</a>: Founded by Rebecca Borough in 2016, Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company based in Los Angeles. Knit Marketing has helped numerous companies grow their social media presence by bringing together a diverse Gen Z and Millennial team to target specific markets and create unique viral content.

</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>10 Things We Learned at the Get Stuff Done Conference</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/10-things-we-learned-at-the-get-stuff-done-conference/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 13 Dec 2017 15:50:43 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=849</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h3>Intro:</h3>
On December 9, 2017, we invited guests to join us at our first Get Stuff Done Digital Marketing Strategy Conference in Downtown Los Angeles. We heard from <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/get-stuff-done-conference-speakers/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">guest speakers</a> all about Brand Storyline, Podcasts, Instagram Stories, Chatbots, YouTube, and Webinars. Guests were given a workbook to help guide their learning throughout the day, and were able to have in-depth discussions with the speakers and fellow attendees. We'll be publishing a lot more about the conference in the coming weeks, but we wanted to give you a glimpse of what we learned at the conference.

[caption id="attachment_860" align="aligncenter" width="718"]<img class="wp-image-860" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/IMG_9198-1024x682.jpg" alt="" width="718" height="478" /> PC: <a href="https://www.instagram.com/sabrinamiso/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Sabrina Miso</a>[/caption]
<h1>10 Things We Learned at the Get Stuff Done Conference</h1>
<h2><span style="color: #8ec11a;"><em>By #TeamKnit</em></span></h2>
<strong>1.</strong> We were given really useful tips on how to get a podcast started by Yolanda Enoch. Check out these awesome <a href="http://www.yolandaenoch.com/start-podcast/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">resources</a>.

<strong>2.</strong> We heard all the different ways we can form our stories from <a href="https://www.pitchgenius.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Jasmine Foroutan</a> such as user lifestyle, mission driven, and personality to name a few.

[caption id="attachment_857" align="alignleft" width="340"]<img class=" wp-image-857" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/IMG_3627-e1513179717276.jpg" alt="" width="340" height="453" /> PC: Robin Borough[/caption]

<strong>3.</strong> There are no shortcuts. Whether you're building a YouTube channel or crafting the perfect Instagram campaign, you have to do the work.

<strong>4.</strong> Email and webinars are not dead, they're actually a great tool for lead generation, from <a href="http://omnikron.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Robin Borough</a>.

<strong>5.</strong> Instagram featured stories are the new BIG thing, according to Marissa Stahl from <a href="http://somethingsocial-la.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Something Social</a>.

<strong>6.</strong> No matter the medium or platform, engagement is still key. It's called "social" media for a reason.

<strong>7.</strong> Speaking of engagement, chat bots are an excellent way to create a unique communication experience for customers, leads, and fans. Benji and Emily from <a href="http://sozango.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">SoZango</a> are really excited about it.

<strong>8.</strong> You have to make quality content and create something you care about in order to build a sustainable YouTube channel, says <a href="http://alecaddd.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Alex Castellani</a>.

<strong>9.</strong> Collaboration is always important. Talking to the speakers and fellow participants really helped develop plans and ideas.

<strong>10.</strong> It feels really good to get stuff done!

Stay tuned for more photos, videos, and updates from our conference and news about future events.

[caption id="attachment_858" align="aligncenter" width="600"]<img class="wp-image-858 size-large" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/IMG_9213-1024x682.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" /> PC: <a href="https://www.instagram.com/sabrinamiso/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Sabrina Miso</a>[/caption]

<hr />

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Happy Holidays</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/happy-holidays/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 23 Dec 2017 21:09:59 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=870</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h1>Happy Holidays!</h1>
Dear Friends,

It's been a fun and full year for Knit Marketing. We've been almost too busy to send holiday cards, but we decided it's important to stop, reflect on the past year, and look forward to the year ahead. This year, we graduated our <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/documenting-history-in-womens-history-month/">first team</a> - now college freshmen, we hired 3 new <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/congratulations-to-knit-marketing-newest-employees/">team members</a>, attended conferences, exhibited at <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/tech-day/">TechDay LA</a>, and even hosted our own <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/10-things-we-learned-at-the-get-stuff-done-conference/">Get Stuff Done Conference</a>. We grew our client base and product offering, and are continuing to grow. Looking ahead to 2018, creating more youth training and job opportunities, and supporting more entrepreneurs and small businesses with their marketing goals. We've been hustling all year, and it doesn't look like there's an end in sight. Good thing our "corporate value" is <em>getting stuff done</em>!

Happy holidays #KnitFriends. You have made Knit Marketing what it is, and we're excited for what's to come! Thank you.

<img class="size-full wp-image-873 aligncenter" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/HappyHolidays.png" alt="" width="528" height="408" />

<hr />

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Rebecca Interviewed by Alessandro Castellani on the Nerd Continuity Podcast</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/interview-with-alessandro-castellani-on-the-nerd-continuity-podcast/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 04 Jan 2018 21:51:57 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=875</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h1>Rebecca Interviewed by Alessandro Castellani on the Nerd Continuity Podcast</h1>
Our new "internet friend," <a href="http://www.alecaddd.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Alex Castellani</a> runs a really cool <a href="https://www.youtube.com/alessandrocastellani" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YouTube</a> channel that offers great tutorials on all things web development. He's become our Mr. Miagi of web development, as he is coaching our whole team on all the waxing on and off that goes into building a website from scratch. He also spoke at our conference in December and you can see his talk <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SKcsb36b0wc" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.
<p style="text-align: left;">Alex also hosts a podcast called <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/nerd-continuity/id1025271701?mt=2" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Nerd Continuity</a> and I had the pleasure of being interviewed on it. Check it out below!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/h4auyQrAWQs?rel=0" width="800" height="450" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"><span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span><span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span><span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span><span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span><span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span><span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span></iframe></p>
If you made it all the way through the interview, you'll notice that I failed when Alex asked me to answer what 3 three words describe me. I thought about this a lot over the next few days and I landed on <strong>dreamer</strong>, <strong>adventurer</strong>, <strong>doer</strong>.

Also, I mentioned a few marketing resources that we read and listen to, so I'm listing them here in case you're interested.
<ul>
 	<li>Awesome daily newsletter <a class="yt-simple-endpoint style-scope yt-formatted-string" href="https://www.youtube.com/redirect?q=https%3A%2F%2Fcarney.co%2Fthe-daily-carnage%2F&amp;redir_token=fMCrBcQva-JLQz946HD9aG-rz-18MTUxNTE4ODM3NUAxNTE1MTAxOTc1&amp;event=video_description&amp;v=h4auyQrAWQs">https://carney.co/the-daily-carnage/</a></li>
 	<li>Great blog posts <a class="yt-simple-endpoint style-scope yt-formatted-string" href="https://www.youtube.com/redirect?q=https%3A%2F%2Fblog.bufferapp.com%2F&amp;redir_token=fMCrBcQva-JLQz946HD9aG-rz-18MTUxNTE4ODM3NUAxNTE1MTAxOTc1&amp;event=video_description&amp;v=h4auyQrAWQs">https://blog.bufferapp.com/</a> (they also have a good podcast.)</li>
 	<li><a class="yt-simple-endpoint style-scope yt-formatted-string" href="https://www.youtube.com/redirect?q=https%3A%2F%2Fblog.hubspot.com%2F&amp;redir_token=fMCrBcQva-JLQz946HD9aG-rz-18MTUxNTE4ODM3NUAxNTE1MTAxOTc1&amp;event=video_description&amp;v=h4auyQrAWQs">https://blog.hubspot.com/</a> - and they also have TONS of templates for anything you might need (email newsletters, press releases, landing pages, etc.)</li>
 	<li><a class="yt-simple-endpoint style-scope yt-formatted-string" href="https://www.youtube.com/redirect?q=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.garyvaynerchuk.com%2F&amp;redir_token=fMCrBcQva-JLQz946HD9aG-rz-18MTUxNTE4ODM3NUAxNTE1MTAxOTc1&amp;event=video_description&amp;v=h4auyQrAWQs">https://www.garyvaynerchuk.com/</a> - this guy is obnoxious but I agree with almost everything he teaches. He has a podcast, a youtube channel, a blog, and a newsletter - so you can choose what you like best.</li>
 	<li><a class="yt-simple-endpoint style-scope yt-formatted-string" href="https://www.youtube.com/redirect?q=https%3A%2F%2Fmastersofscale.com%2F&amp;redir_token=fMCrBcQva-JLQz946HD9aG-rz-18MTUxNTE4ODM3NUAxNTE1MTAxOTc1&amp;event=video_description&amp;v=h4auyQrAWQs">https://mastersofscale.com/</a> podcast, which isn't necessarily about marketing but it's excellent. Lots of great interviews.</li>
 	<li>For general social media stuff I recommend 2 books:
<ul>
 	<li>Likeable Social Media: <a class="yt-simple-endpoint style-scope yt-formatted-string" href="https://www.youtube.com/redirect?q=http%3A%2F%2Famzn.to%2F2C650PE&amp;redir_token=fMCrBcQva-JLQz946HD9aG-rz-18MTUxNTE4ODM3NUAxNTE1MTAxOTc1&amp;event=video_description&amp;v=h4auyQrAWQs">http://amzn.to/2C650PE</a></li>
 	<li>The Dragonfly Effect: <a class="yt-simple-endpoint style-scope yt-formatted-string" href="https://www.youtube.com/redirect?q=http%3A%2F%2Famzn.to%2F2C45mpX&amp;redir_token=fMCrBcQva-JLQz946HD9aG-rz-18MTUxNTE4ODM3NUAxNTE1MTAxOTc1&amp;event=video_description&amp;v=h4auyQrAWQs">http://amzn.to/2C45mpX</a> (this one is more nonprofit and social enterprise focused)</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
Thanks for watching/listening! Hope you enjoyed it. Stay tuned for more updates about our conference and other fun Knit news.

-Rebecca

<hr />

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>How to Start a Podcast with Yolanda Enoch</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/starting-a-podcast-yolanda-enoch-get-stuff-done-marketing-conference/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 15 Jan 2018 23:44:25 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=890</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Knit Marketing's Get Stuff Done Conference Presents:</span></h3>
<h1><span style="font-weight: 400;">How to Start a Podcast with Yolanda Enoch</span></h1>
<h2><span style="color: #ff00ff;"><em>By Yesenia Gomez</em></span></h2>
&nbsp;
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/VwrUliLaXIU" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></h1>
&nbsp;

At our Get Stuff Done Conference, we were so lucky to learn about podcasting with <a href="http://yolandaenoch.com">Yolanda Enoch</a>, who hosts a podcast called <a href="http://www.yolandaenoch.com/podcast" target="_blank" rel="noopener">How She Did It</a>! We took a ride learning about how Yolanda got to where she is with her podcast and learned some tips along the way for starting our own. Among the tips we learned, was the importance of timing that a lot of people may take for granted. Although it is possible to make a podcast in a day, it takes a lot more than we think.

Not only is it hard to hear our own voices on recording, but we also need <strong>research</strong>!<strong> </strong>It is important to conduct research, not only about the industry, but about you too, what is best for you to base your podcast on. Time to <strong>experiment</strong> with the podcasts takes a lot of time especially when you need extra time to make sure you <strong>create quality content</strong>. Yolanda took almost two years to release her first podcast! Another big thing to take away from Yolanda's presentation was <strong>managing</strong> <strong>costs</strong>. Although it may make sense to spend a lot to make a quality podcast, that is not what is needed. An expensive microphone does not necessarily mean more quality content, your own earphones work just fine! Quality content relies on what you talk about, your message and lessons you teach to your audience.

After all, you may feel starting a podcast is not for you, still the best way to know is the <strong>commit to six</strong>! We learned from Yolanda that it is a good strategy to attempt making 6 podcasts. After that, you should evaluate if it is actually for you.

<em>Connect with Yolanda on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/yolandaenoch" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>, email here <a href="mailto:hi@yolandaenoch.com">here</a>, or follow her on Instagram, Twitter, and Facebook at @yolandaenoch.</em>

<hr />

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Using Webinars for Lead Generation with Robin Borough</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/using-webinars-for-lead-generation-with-robin-borough/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 23 Jan 2018 01:04:11 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=892</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Knit Marketing's Get Stuff Done Conference Presents:</span></h3>
<h1><span style="font-weight: 400;">How to Use Webinars for Lead Generation with Robin Borough</span></h1>
<h2><span style="color: #ff00ff;"><em>By Yesenia Gomez</em></span></h2>
&nbsp;
<h1 style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0px auto; text-align: center;"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/L1M74ynXt5k" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></h1>
<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">

&nbsp;

Our mom and our number one fan is the only one who can make learning about webinars fun! To be more specific, we learned about creating a loyal fan base by using webinars. Robin Borough, president of <a href="http://omnikron.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Omnikron</a>, walked us through the whole process of using webinars from setting it up before, to tips for during the webinar and how to follow up after.

Starting at <em>before the webinar,</em> we learned about investigating our audience and inviting them to the webinar by using email tools and direct messaging. Robin also took the time to walk us through the actual webinars, because although it can seem outdated, we learned how to keep it modern and interesting to keep our audience engaged. We kept note of tips on timing, pitching and overall keeping the conversation rich and full of knowledge for the audience! Another big thing we learned is what to do after the event ends using our assets! For example Zoom has options to download the mp3 file from the webinar (isn't that awesome?!), and with that you can do a bunch of things, like start a podcast maybe? Lastly, we explored the follow-up options to keep in touch with your audience in the most effective manner, invite them to your next events, and also keep them as fans!

<em>Connect with Robin on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/robinborough/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a> or email her <a href="mailto:Robin.Borough@Omnikron.com">here</a>. </em>

<hr />

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>
</div>]]></content:encoded>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=896</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h3>Intro:</h3>
Jorge, Nyana, and Yesenia were invited to attend and help out with the social media for the Moja Moja Benefit Concert this year. They had a great time listening to the artists, admiring all the fashionable guests, and learning more about Moja Moja's social impact initiatives.

<img class="size-full wp-image-917 aligncenter" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/IMG_5815-1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="800" />
<h1><span style="font-weight: 400;">MOJA MOJA Benefit Concert 2018</span></h1>
<h2><span style="color: #0066ff;"><em>By Jorge Guevara</em></span></h2>
<span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="http://themojamoja.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">MOJA MOJA</a> held their annual brunch and benefit concert on February 10th this year. The hosts of the event did a fantastic job with amazing food, music, and a great venue.</span>

<img class="wp-image-918 alignleft" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Snapchat-313764482-1.jpg" alt="" width="295" height="295" />

</div>
<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">

<span style="font-weight: 400;">MOJA MOJA is a foundation set out on </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">supporting businesses and nonprofits helping multicultural youth to pursue education, internships and job preparedness opportunities in STEAM fields.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">We’ll be interviewing some of those young minds later this summer. We hope wish them good luck</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The event had some fantastic performances by the likes of Wajatta, Jungle Fire, Elise Trouw, and The Steoples. This accompanied by delicious brunch created a relaxed and enjoyable ambience.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The MOJA MOJA foundation also awarded The Revolution, will.i.am., and Beat Junkie Sound each for their contributions to society.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">We can't wait for next year's benefit concert!</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">-Jorge</span>
<div>

<hr />

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>
</div>]]></content:encoded>
