	<item>
		<title>A Guide to YouTube with Alex Castellani</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/a-guide-to-youtube-with-alex-castellani/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 30 Jan 2018 00:31:42 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=932</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Knit Marketing's Get Stuff Done Conference Presents:</span></h3>
<h1><span style="font-weight: 400;">A Guide to YouTube with Alex Castellani</span></h1>
<h2><span style="color: #ff00ff;"><em>By Yesenia Gomez</em></span></h2>
&nbsp;
<p style="text-align: center;"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/2cXJGa9_44o" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="http://alecaddd.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Alex</a> is our YouTube goals! But like he himself said, not because he is famous or rich, but because of how his channel started. We recommend you hear the story from him (by watching the video above), because we were very inspired! But long story short, Alex learned a new language while teaching others what he knows, coding! In the long run, he'll be rich because of this! </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">In his previous job, he was unable to climb higher because of his lack of language to explain things, and by using YouTube to teach and learn at the same time, this was no longer a problem. Alex was able to tell us his story and taught us about the mistakes he made to give us tips to start a YouTube channel. He explained the process of settling on a topic for a channel by teaching us how he got to his topic by narrowing all his skills and analyzing his YouTube statistics, and in the end he landed on something that was authentic, interesting to him, and something useful to viewers. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">By hearing Alex’s story, we learned many more tips and busted many YouTube myths. We busted "quantity over quality," because that only can work in the short term; the truth is less is more. We learned the importance of engaging with your audience, the benefits of YouTube partnerships, focusing on what you care about, and not getting wrapped up in the current trends. Best of all, during the breakout session we got to write a long term strategy for a channel we want to start with Alex's guidance. </span>

<i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Follow Alex on </span></i><a href="https://www.youtube.com/user/williamprey"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">YouTube</span></i></a><i><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and </span></i><a href="https://twitter.com/alecaddd"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Twitter</span></i></a><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">, and connect with him on </span></i><a href="https://www.facebook.com/alecadddpage"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Facebook</span></i></a><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">. </span></i>

<hr />

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>How To Use Instagram Stories with Marissa Stahl</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/how-to-use-instagram-stories-with-marissa-stahl/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 06 Feb 2018 00:34:24 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=934</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Knit Marketing's Get Stuff Done Conference Presents:</span></h3>
<h1><span style="font-weight: 400;">How to use Instagram Stories for Your Brand with Marissa Stahl</span></h1>
<h2><span style="color: #ff00ff;"><em>By Yesenia Gomez</em></span></h2>
&nbsp;
<p style="text-align: center;"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/F1RdS7ugk1k" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Social media is constantly changing, we see new platforms frequently arising and old ones adding new features so quickly that it can be confusing and overwhelming to deal with. Luckily, we had Marissa Stahl from <a href="http://www.somethingsocial-la.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Something Social</a> at the conference to keep us updated and teach us some cool hacks to optimize our social media presences. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">First off, we learned about Marissa and her team that encourage caption creativity, brand cultivating and believe hard work should go into understanding your vision and values. We have to admit, we were all a bit confused by the new algorithms and features on Instagram such as Instastories! Marissa gave us tips to effectively use pictures, videos and boomerangs to increase our social media attention and to tell our stories. She gave us helpful ideas and examples for content that should be specific to our company. We loved all she taught us about the secrets of geotags and hashtags that are a key to engagement! She went even further in discussing how to conduct Instagram polls and using Direct Messages to form a community around our brands and how we can highlight an important item on our accounts. </span>

<em>Email Marissa <a href="mailto:marissa@somethingsocial-la.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a> and follow her on Instagram and Twitter <a href="http://twitter.com/marissacstahl" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@marissacstahl</a>. </em>

<hr />

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Using Chatbots for Marketing with SoZango Solutions</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/using-chatbots-for-marketing-with-sozango-solutions/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 13 Feb 2018 00:38:34 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=937</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Knit Marketing's Get Stuff Done Conference Presents:</span></h3>
<h1><span style="font-weight: 400;">ChatBots with SoZango's Benji Rostoker and Emily Mischel</span></h1>
<h2><span style="color: #ff00ff;"><em>By Yesenia Gomez</em></span></h2>
&nbsp;
<p style="text-align: center;"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/CQNbPfj_TJ8" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">It was so fun and crazy to learn about chatbots with <a href="http://sozango.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">SoZango Solutions</a>! They are really the future. At the Get Stuff Done Conference, we explored why chatbots are so useful to engage with customers in a personalized way. We learned in the best way, through first-hand experience by getting to play with some of the chatbots SoZango themselves have made! The different places to apply chatbots were surprising and their benefits seemed endless. Bots can help a lot with promotion, sales, customer service, data collection and internal efficiencies. Not only are they super helpful for the company using them, but they also provide a good, entertaining and painless experience for the user. Emily and Benji answered all the questions we had, which were a lot because chatbots are new and revolutionary! </span>

<i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Talk to us about conversations SO worth having </span></i><a href="https://www.facebook.com/SoZangoSolutions/"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">@sozangosolutions</span></i></a><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></i>

<hr />

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

&nbsp;

</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Telling Your Brand Story with Jasmine Foroutan</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/telling-your-brand-story-with-jasmine-foroutan/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 20 Feb 2018 00:43:05 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=940</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Knit Marketing's Get Stuff Done Conference Presents:</span></h3>
<h1><span style="font-weight: 400;">A Brand Story with Jasmine Foroutan</span></h1>
<h2><span style="color: #ff00ff;"><em>By Yesenia Gomez</em></span></h2>
&nbsp;
<p style="text-align: center;"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/6inPMQ1VAAs" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p>
&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Jasmine from <a href="http://pitchgenius.co" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Pitch Genius</a> was the expert to teach us all about developing our brand stories during the Get Stuff Done Conference. She took us through writing and perfecting our own pitches that are very important for every aspect of a business. We clarified and worded our goals and visions into a quick catchy phrase that properly incorporates what our business stands for and how we want people to view our message. Using our content, research and design we were able to design the perfect storyline. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">It was helpful to learn how to conduct research involving competition branding and getting to know our own customers. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">One of the best parts of Jasmine’s presentation was learning the variety of storylines possible; there is not just one cookie cutter way to create a storyline. There is a spectrum for storytelling and what fits best for you depending on your company. For example there is the hero, team and mission revolved lines. Using all her tips everyone was able to enhance and write their pitches! You can see the whole thing in the video above. Big thank you to Jasmine! </span>

<i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Follow Jasmine on </span></i><a href="https://medium.com/@PitchGenius_Co"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Medium</span></i></a><i><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and </span></i><a href="http://www.twitter.com/pitchgenius_co"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Twitter</span></i></a><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">, connect on </span></i><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jasmine-foroutan/"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">LinkedIn</span></i></a><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">, and learn about pitch deck services at </span></i><a href="http://www.pitchgenius.co/"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">www.pitchgenius.co</span></i></a><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Feel free to email her </span></i><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">here</span></i><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">.  </span></i>

<hr />

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Meet Female Founder: Taryn Rose</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/meet-female-founder-taryn-rose/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 03 Mar 2018 20:40:34 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=981</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Stepping Into Success with Taryn Rose</span></h1>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #ffd700;"><em style="font-size: 16px;">By Adewole Williams</em></span></h1>
<img class=" wp-image-982 aligncenter" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Taryn-Rose-1024x925.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="438" />

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">This month we’re featuring strong, independent, and intelligent women. For March, Women's History Month, we’re happy to present one of Knit Marketing’s clients, Taryn Rose. She’s the founder of Taryn Rose and founder/CEO of Enrico Cuini, two widely successful luxury shoe companies. I had the pleasure of attending an event with Taryn at a Central City Neighborhood Partners event, where she was gifting work shoes for independent working women.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Taryn’s story is a unique one and is sure to inspire and motivate. She started her first company in her garage and was able to grow it to a 40 million dollar company in 10 years.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">She learned to be resourceful from her father who was a physician in Vietnam, and when he moved their family to the US to escape the war, had to find a way to continue to work. Fast forward years later, to Taryn becoming an Orthopedic Surgeon herself. She never let anything stop her from her pursuit of a great education, or of looking her best! A stiletto enthusiast, she wanted to create shoes that looked fashionable, and also properly supported a woman’s feet.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">In her 2012 TED talk, she mentioned some of the key traits that she’s lived by, that have made her a successful entrepreneur: Vulnerability, Love, and Courage. Many of the women at the CCNP event were immigrants or from immigrant families, so Taryn’s story was especially relatable and inspirational to them. She was vulnerable enough to show not only the business side of her but also her personal side. Lastly, she showed copious amounts of love, by not just giving away shoes, but giving the women hope, and affirming the dreams and goals that they had for themselves as well. Thank you, Taryn, for your example of what it means to be a strong and powerful business Woman!</span>

<hr />

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Meet Female Founder: Rebecca Borough</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/meet-female-founder-rebecca-borough/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 24 Mar 2018 21:30:14 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=985</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h1 style="text-align: center;"> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Knitting Together a Bright Future
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">with </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Rebecca Borough</span></h1>
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #ffd700;"><em>By Adewole Williams</em></span></h2>
<img class="wp-image-986 aligncenter" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Knit_Marketing_GSD_Conference-6-678x1024.jpg" alt="" width="280" height="703" />

<span style="font-weight: 400;">We’re wrapping up our weekly features of boss ladies for women’s history month with the woman responsible for bringing you engaging, educational, and useful content; none other than Knit Marketing founder Rebecca Borough! Rebecca has worked tirelessly to be a resource, and beacon of hope to other entrepreneurs, and startups by sharing her knowledge and bringing like-minds together to engage in conversation and be a catalyst for the next big idea.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">After college, Rebecca worked as a platinum event coordinator with Exquisite Events. She loved seeing how all the details came together to complete a grand vision. Soon, however, she wanted to see how the other side lived; the majority of the world. This led her to join the Peace Corps. She taught English and was a small business volunteer for two years in the state Hidalgo, Mexico. After finishing up there, the real fun began!</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Rebecca decided to start her own business upon her return to the United States, and attended USC Marshall's Social Entrepreneurship program to learn how to do it right. She wanted to start a business that would have more than profit as a bottom line. Knit Marketing was then born! Combining her love of entrepreneurship with teaching and education, Knit Marketing's platform is double-edged. On the one hand, Knit makes money by providing premier digital marketing and social media services to our clients, but we're also able to have a social impact by preparing young adults with work experience, training, and the tools needed to be competitive in today’s job market.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">So far Rebecca and Team Knit have been knocking it out of the park! Since starting the business, Rebecca has hired 4 young adults as interns and one full-time employee. The company is growing by the day and is accomplishing all this while maintaining our very important social mission. Empowering youth!</span>

<hr />

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>
</div>
]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Meet Female Founder: Cecilia Sibony</title>

		<pubDate>Sat, 10 Mar 2018 22:16:33 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>

		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h3></h3>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Get Stuff Done Webinar Series:
Being a Lady Boss with Cecilia Sibony</span></h1>
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #ffd700;"><em>By Adewole Williams</em></span></h2>
&nbsp;

<a href="http://sesamaise.com">Sesamaise Tahini</a> founder Cecilia Sibony shares with us the intriguing story of the creation of her company. She speaks on some of the many hurdles she faced and gives some sound advice to aspiring entrepreneurs. Watch the full Webinar above to learn more about her story.

<hr />

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Women&#039;s History Month: Female Founders &amp; Entrepreneurs</title>
		<link>http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/womens-history-month-female-founders-entrepreneurs/</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 31 Mar 2018 22:40:38 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/?p=994</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h1 style="text-align: center;">Women's History Month:
Female Founders &amp; Entrepreneurs</h1>
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #ffd700;"><em>By Adewole Williams</em></span></h2>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1002 aligncenter" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/strong-women.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="587" />

March was Women’s History Month, so we highlighted some strong and powerful businesswomen in our network who are doing amazing things! We’ve featured these women because of their business tenacity, know-how, and perseverance. They all have a social mission tied into the inner workings of their company. Whether it's bringing business owners on opposite sides to the table to work toward Middle East peace, or gifting shoes to working women so that they can be comfortable while pursuing their own dreams, these women deserve recognition!


<p style="text-align: center;">Click on the links below to learn more about the Female Founders we've highlighted this month.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/meet-female-founder-taryn-rose/"><strong>Taryn Rose - Founder of Taryn Rose &amp; Enrico Cuini</strong></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/using-webinars-for-lead-generation-with-robin-borough/"><strong>Robin Borough - President of Omnikron Solutions</strong></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/meet-female-founder-cecilia-sibony/"><strong>Cecilia Sibony - Founder of Sesamaise Tahini</strong></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/blog/meet-female-founder-rebecca-borough/"><strong>Rebecca Borough - Founder of Knit Marketing</strong></a></p>


<hr />

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>
</div>]]></content:encoded>

		<dc:creator><![CDATA[knitmarketing]]></dc:creator>

		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<div style="max-width: 800px; float: none; margin: 0 auto;">
<h1 style="text-align: center;">Welcome to the team (AGAIN) to
Adewole Williams!</h1>
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #ffd700;"><em>By Rebecca Borough</em></span></h2>
<img class="size-full wp-image-1015 aligncenter" src="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Adewole.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="397" />

It was so natural to just keep working with Adewole, that we didn't even take a second to pause to<strong> thank him</strong>, and <strong>congratulate</strong> him for his promotion! On February 19th, Adewole became Knit's first full-time employee and Operations Manager and we couldn't be more pleased to have him on board.

In the past year, as project manager, Adewole has helped us with countless video editing projects, attended conferences and events, and managed multiple social media accounts and is now helping us lay the ground work for scaling Knit Marketing. I agree with his girlfriend, Cassie, that we are making history!

In addition to being an amazing support to Knit Marketing, Adewole also writes and produces his own music as <a href="https://www.facebook.com/GraphikLA/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Graphik LA</a>. He'll make it big soon we're sure... but hopefully not too soon, as we'd like to keep him around for a little while. ;)

<hr />

<em>Knit Marketing is a digital marketing company dedicated to helping companies bring their marketing dreams to life. <a href="http://e46.008.myftpupload.com/contact-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contact us</a> for more information. </em>

</div>
</div>]]></content:encoded>
